title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter pie plate.
Fill with apples; sprinkle on cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Heat oil and brown pork chops. Pour off fat and set aside. Add soup and water to pan. bring to a boil and return chops to pan. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until chops are no longer pink.

title: barbecue short ribs
directions: Mix together vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, red pepper, paprika, chili powder, catsup and water.
Pour over ribs and sliced onion in Dutch oven.
Cook for 2 hours over low heat.

title: country club squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and trim off ends.
Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Drain again. Combine squash, sour cream, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, margarine and paprika.
Sprinkle over squash mixture.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello, sugar and cornstarch, then add water and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool in refrigerator.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Very good.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Put all ingredients in a double boiler and melt (stirring often).
Spoon into bonbon cups.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften outside fridge for about 20 minutes. Mix together all ingredients until well blended and form into a ball (or 2 small balls).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil hen until tender in water seasoned with onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and reserve all stock.
Chop onion and bell pepper; combine soups and grated cheese.
Just before putting casserole together, soak the frozen tortillas in boiling chicken stock until wilted.

Start layering casserole in 9 x 12-inch baking dish in following order: tortillas, chicken, onion, bell pepper, soup mixture and cheese. Repeat the layers, being sure the tortillas are oozing with the stock.
Cover the casserole with the Ro-Tel tomatoes and all the juice.
Juice in the casserole should be about half the depth of the dish, if not, add a little more stock.
Make at least 1 day ahead, so that the juices will blend.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese on medium speed 2 minutes, until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating on medium 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time; beat until yellow just disappears. Gradually add flour and mix on low speed until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings, nuts and butterscotch morsels. Spoon into greased and floured 12-cup tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool completely.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Combine broccoli, soup, milk, butter and dry onion mix.
Mix into a large skillet; bring to boil over medium heat. Lower heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice; heat jar of cheese.
Pour into mixture.
Pour into greased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oh so rich lasagna
directions: Preheat over to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat, drain and add sauce and let simmer.
Mix egg with ricotta cheese and set aside. Cook noodles in water and a little oil until tender.
Spray bottom of pan with oil and sprinkle with salt.
Layer as follows: noodles, most of sauce, noodles, ricotta cheese, noodles, rest of sauce and mozzarella cheese.
Bake about 40 minutes in 9 x 13 glass dish.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Mix together nuts and raisins and coat with some of the flour. Mix all other ingredients together, then add nuts and raisins and mix.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mint punch
directions: Mix all juices with mint and sugar.
Stir well to dissolve. Add sodas, sherbet and berries.
Chill well.
Serves approximately 45 (6 ounce) glasses or about 2 gallons.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In saucepan, cook carrots, covered in small amount of lightly salted water, until just tender (15 minutes).
Add green pepper; cover and cook 3 minutes more.
Drain.
Drain the pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to make 1/3 cup of liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in pineapple liquid, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and pineapple.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in buttered 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and spread over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt margarine and add onions and broccoli.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then add cheese and stir until melted.
Add mushrooms and almonds; stir until heated.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: blueberry (or other fruit) cheesecake
directions: Blend the graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter well.
Pat firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and 2 cups sugar while preparing crust.
Put on crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Remove bone and skin from chicken and chop.
Arrange in a greased 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Make thin gravy with broth, flour and chicken fat.
Pour 3/4 of gravy over chicken.
Make dressing with dry bread, salt, melted oleo, sage, chopped onion and cream combined.
Arrange dressing over chicken and gravy, then pour remainder of gravy over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rose's vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and Imperial granulated sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs, coconut, pecans, cherries and vanilla flavoring.
Put in well-greased and floured 9-inch angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275° or until done.
Let cake cool thoroughly in pan (at least 6 hours) before removing from pan.

title: pineapple fingers
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cake mix, egg yolks, butter and flavoring.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in coconut and pineapple. Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into finger strips.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Begin recipe just before serving.

title: potato patch casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and seasoning.
Mix potatoes, peas and carrots in bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Add hamburger and cover with cheese sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until done.
Drain.
Saute onion in margarine; add cheese and stir until melted.
Add soup.
Put 3/4 cup stuffing mix in dish.
Add cabbage.
Pour cheese mixture over cabbage and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese bone cookies for dogs
directions: Combine flour, cheese, garlic & oil in food processor. Whirl until mixture is consistency of corn meal, with machine running slowly add water until mixture forms into a ball.

title: piccalilli
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions thin, then let stand overnight. Drain next morning.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Add tomatoes and onions; bring to boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Mix in the remaining ingredients, constantly stirring. Spoon onto wax paper.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: spicy honey chicken wings
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart baking dish. Add chicken wings and toss to coat; cover and refrigerate 1 hour. Uncover dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done. Serves 8.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Skin tomatoes and cut into quarters. Slice peppers into strips. Slice onion into thin rings. Arrange vegetables into neat sections in a large Pyrex bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and boil furiously for one minute. Pour over vegetables. Cool slightly and refrigerate. Just before serving, sliced cucumbers can be added.

title: grustoli
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add lemon juice and dry ingredients.
Roll out dough as for very, very thin pie crust. Strips should be 2 1/2-inches wide, any length.
Cut crosswise, sort of like a diamond shape.
Fry in hot oil.
Turn quickly, as these cook fast.
Remove and sprinkle with sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken. Add soup, water, paprika and pepper. Stir; heat to a boil. Stir in rice and broccoli. Top with chicken. Cook on low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease bottom of pan with shortening.
Put a layer of onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and celery.
Brown chicken on both sides. Place chicken on top of vegetables.
Bring 1 cup of rice and water to boiling.
Pour over top of chicken.
Add chicken gumbo soup. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt as desired.
Add a little of the onion soup mix.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: greek lamb stew
directions: Saute onions and lamb in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce, water, bouillon, oregano, marjoram, pepper, bay leaf and garlic.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add green pepper and eggplant.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato wedges and olives; simmer 5 minutes.
Ladle into bowls and garnish with sour cream and sprinkle with paprika.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding into pan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk; cook for 1 minute.
Mix in peanut butter.
Mix in a separate bowl the oatmeal and vanilla.
Pour heated mixture over oatmeal mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Can be refrigerated.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: De-joint chicken wings, discarding bony tips.
Place meatier parts in shallow baking pan.
Combine soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and water and heat it until sugar and butter dissolve. Pour over chicken and bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
This is also very good over chicken breasts and works very well in the crockpot.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots, green pepper and onion in a bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pan.
Heat to dissolve sugar, then cool.
Pour marinade over the vegetables.

title: boiled custard
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk and cook in double boiler until mixture coats the spoon.
Add vanilla and chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In frypan, cook onion in butter or margarine 10 minutes. Add chili, corn and tomatoes. Mix well until blended. Pour into 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Prepare corn muffin dough according to package directions. Stir cheese into dough. Spoon dough around edge of baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polish italian pierogies
directions: Drain the shells, prepared as directed. (Note: Adding 1 tablespoon oil to water when preparing shells will help prevent sticking.) Add 1 onion, grated, to mashed potatoes (your favorite recipe). Gently fill shells with mashed potato mixture. Cook 5 onions, diced, in a medium skillet over medium-high heat until they begin to brown. Melt 3 tablespoons margarine
in large skillet over medium heat. Carefully place stuffed shells in skillet and cook over medium heat until brown on bottoms. Serve with browned onions.

title: one bowl pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in one bowl.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until springs back. Cool on plate and serve.

title: calabrese chicken (or rabbit)
directions: Cut chicken or rabbit into pieces. Brown in olive oil in heavy-duty Dutch oven. Add garlic, either crushed or whole, peppers, olives (drained), oregano (1 teaspoon or to taste) and rosemary (2 pinches). Turn down to simmer. Cover and cook for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken appears dark and ready to fall apart.

title: cabbage and kielbasa soup
directions: Saute onion in olive oil slightly.
Add cabbage and cook for a few minutes. Add flour and mix well. Add wine and beef stock. Bring to a boil (boiling gets rid of the alcohol in the wine, but leaves a terrific flavor).
While simmering, add spices. Salt and pepper to taste.
After soup is ready, add kielbasa and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: corn puffle
directions: Frozen corn can be used.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat; season. Peel and slice potatoes thin. In a casserole, put a layer of beef, then layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle onions and cheese; repeat layers. Pour soup over all. Bake at 400° (high) until potatoes are done.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and steam until pliable, about 5 minutes.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaves.
Cover with spaghetti sauce diluted with water.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and butter.
Add buttermilk; mix real good.
Fold in vanilla, lemon extract and coconut.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 minutes.
Do not open oven until time is completely up.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 cups.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mince the pepper, onion and celery (I use food processor). Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole and bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes. Do not cover. Serve with rice or angel hair pasta.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie crust.
Prick top with fork.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, until crust is brown.
Let stand 3 minutes before cutting.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dark cake
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch cake pan, mix all dry ingredients.
Do not grease pan. Make 3 little pockets in the mix.
Place vinegar, oil and vanilla in each pocket.
Pour water over everything and mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops dijon
directions: In a small bowl combine salad dressing, mustard and pepper. Brush mixture on both sides of chops.
In a skillet, cook chops on medium for 20 minutes.
Turn chops and add onion rings.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, gradually beating until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients except for candy bars and mix thoroughly.
Stir in candy and place in ice cream freezer to freeze.
(You may need to add additional milk to fill line of ice cream freezer.)

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first five ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in butter.
Remove onion from butter, grate cheese and combine with beans and soup in casserole dish. Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges, about 1/2 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces and brown; remove from pan. Brown chicken.
Return sausage to pan.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat until rice is done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O with the instant pudding in boiling water.
Set jello, but not hard.
Mix in the drained mandarin oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in mold and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and sugar.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: baked chicken with cornbread dressing
directions: Saute celery, onion and
parsley in the margarine until tender.
Mix all together with
enough broth to make nice soft texture.
Bake
dressing
about
one
hour
at
Season chicken as desired and bake one hour or until completely done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
I often replace some of mayonnaise and sour cream with plain yogurt.
This is also good on baked potatoes.

title: ice tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags. Cover and steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags, squeezing them gently. Stir in sugar and lemonade concentrate. Set tea aside to cool. Stir in ginger ale just before serving. Serve over ice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely. Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water and add strawberries.
Set this mixture in refrigerator until it is thick. (Allow at least 3 hours for this.)
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzels.
Add strawberry mixture. Refrigerate until serving.

title: wetback special
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine with one onion, garlic, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper, and chili beans. Simmer for 2 hours.
Assemble on a plate by layers.
Fritos, sauce, lettuce, grated cheese, chopped onions, and dried tomatoes. Top with sour cream and avocado slice if desired.
Makes 10-12 servings.

title: mixed greens sauté
directions: In a large saute pan, add mixed greens, olive oil and garlic. Cook until slightly wilted and serve. Serves 2.

title: coco-nut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until it forms stiff peaks.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased paper bag (reversed) that has been placed on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 23 minutes at 300°.

title: fresh tuna hero
directions: * To roast bell pepper, halve, core and seed them.
Flatten with your hand and place, skin side up, on foil on a baking sheet. Broil about 3-inches from the heat until skins blacken and are charred.
Remove to a paper bag and close up for 15 minutes to steam.
Rub off the charred skin.

title: breast of chicken with artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Bring
chicken, celery, onions, salt and pepper to boil in
1 quart
water.
Reduce
heat;
simmer
until breasts are tender. Strain broth and let it cool.
When breasts are cool, skin	and chop
into	round slices.
Wash and slice mushrooms horizontally into
round
slices.
Saute
in
butter
and add grated onion and lemon juice.

title: no fail microwave divinity
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cook in microwave oven for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Candy thermometer should read 260°; if not, cook one or two minutes longer.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except rhubarb, and let stand while preparing the crust. Pour mixture over rhubarb in shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until done.

title: cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Cream the
cream cheese. Add salad dressing and pineapple and cream
together.
Add nuts.
Spread on slices of whole wheat bread or bread of choice.

title: green chili pie
directions: Open chilies up and clean out seeds and seams.
Lay out chilies flat in bottom of a 9-inch Pyrex pie plate (like a pie crust).
Put cheese over chilies up to the rim.
Mix beaten eggs and other ingredients.
Slowly spoon eggs over cheese.
Bake in a preheated 275° oven for 45 minutes.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until well blended.
Serve warm with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: salted pecans
directions: Soak pecans in salted water for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towel for 2 hours.
Bake in 300° oven, stirring every 10 minutes until of desired color of brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell; bake in 350° oven (325° for glass pie plate) for 50 minutes or until brown and set.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream 1 cup butter, 2 cups sugar and chocolate.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking powder, dash of salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and buttermilk.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Bake in layer pans for 30 minutes or tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Mix remaining sugar, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Add dash of salt and evaporated milk.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Beat until creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: untossed tossed salad
directions: Place layer of spinach in large bowl.
Press.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and bacon.
Add eggs and lettuce layer.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add peas and onion.
Mix mayonnaise with sour cream.
Cover salad with mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least a few hours.

title: butter mints
directions: Blend all ingredients; knead color as desired.
Form into small balls.
Press down.
Let dry for at least 1 day before packaging.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cocoa.
Add hot water and beat. Sift flour, soda and baking powders.
Stir in mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Over medium heat, mix sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir.
Serve over biscuits.

title: hospitality pie
directions: Brown coconut and nuts in oven with 1 stick oleo.
Stir often. Cool.
Mix cheese, milk and Cool Whip.
Pour half into each pie shell.
Pour topping over each half and cover with rest of mixture.
Drizzle caramel on top of pies.
Freeze before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 1 day in refrigerator.

title: black eyes peas
directions: Cook meat until fat is rendered.
Transfer meat to 6 to 8 quart pot.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in meat drippings.
Pour peas into pot.
Add all sauted vegetables and Rotel tomatoes to pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook over medium to medium-low heat for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pie filling and stir in pineapple plus the juice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish and congeal.
It only takes a little time to congeal.

title: chicken with apples
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in gallon size food storage bag. Add chicken and share until coated.
Reserve 2 tablespoons flour mixture.
Heat oil in large deep skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook 5 to 7 minutes, turning once until well browned. Remove to a plate.
Add onion, celery and carrot to drippings in skillet.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring several times.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons reserved flour and cook 3 minutes longer.
Stir in cider, broth, rosemary and garlic.
Add chicken.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until chicken is done.
Remove to serving platter and cover loosely with foil. Process liquid and vegetables in blender until smooth.
Pour back into skillet; add apples.
Cook over low heat 5 to 7 minutes until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove apples to serving platter. Serve sauce separately.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour milk and bananas.
Sift and stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease a loaf pan; let stand in loaf pan for 20 minutes and then bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Cook onions in oil until soft, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until rice is done.
Toss lightly with fork.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add oatmeal to the mixture; stir.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: carrot cake and cream cheese filling
directions: (Be sure to grate carrots and refrigerate before starting.) Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients 2 or 3 times.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add nuts and carrots, a small amount at a time, until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans (three 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup melted butter with the next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: apricot pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and jello in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until jello is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Mix these ingredients well, but do not beat.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping. Chill until firm.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add tuna, mushrooms and soup.
Place cheese throughout casserole, creating layers evenly.
Bake at 350° about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Make spaghetti according to package directions.
Cool spaghetti and add remaining ingredients.

title: whiskey slushes
directions: Melt the sugar in the tea.
Mix all other ingredients and freeze.
(This takes 24 hours.)
Serve by scooping out some into a glasss and pouring a small amount of Mountain Dew over it.

title: vegetable soup to can or freeze
directions: Fry hamburger with onions.
Add all remaining ingredients. Mix and fill cans.
Pressure cook for 3/4 hour or cold pack 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy paella
directions: Remove meat from casing.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook sausage and drumsticks in hot oil, stirring to break it up. Spoon off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix apple juice, onion and mushroom sauce together.
Pour over chicken parts.
Put 1 cup mushrooms over the top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Put foil over top.
Thicken your sauce for gravy.

title: hot swiss chard salad
directions: Marinate garlic clove in oil for 1 hour; remove garlic.
Wash, dry and tear chard into bite-size pieces (remove stems).
Just before serving, heat oil, vinegar, salt and pepper, stirring occasionally.
Pour over chard; toss until well coated.
Sprinkle with eggs and bacon.
Toss lightly.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices, if desired.

title: stuffed puff pastry(banh pate chaud)
directions: Prepare puff pastry shells as box instructions.
Remove from oven and set aside.
In a large skillet, brown pork for about 10 minutes.
Drain all fat.
Add in all ingredients to the cooked pork.
Cook with medium-low heat for 5 minutes.
Fill pastry with pork.
Serve immediately.

title: plum quick bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the eggs, baby food, oil and buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the egg mixture and beat just until moistened.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt oleo in long 13x9 inch pan.
Add each of the remaining ingredients in the order listed spreading on top of each other. Do not stir.
Bake at 350 degrees.
Let it cook about 25 minutes. Cut up in one inch squares.

title: mary's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Add alternately with sour cream.
Mix just until combined.
Stir in water.
Pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: In a large bowl grate potatoes, let stand 5 minutes, top may turn color, but ignore.
Remove as much excess liquid as possible. Add egg and mix well, then sprinkle flour while mixing.
In a well-oiled heated skillet, to check drop a bit of potato mixture in and if sizzles, it's ready.
Using a large kitchen spoon full of mixture make pancake size patties.
Fry until top looks dry and bottom is golden brown, turn and fry until golden brown.
Using a spatula, remove pancake, tipping it over pan to remove excess oil.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel eggs.
Combine sausage, parsley, sage and pepper in a large mixing bowl, mixing well.
Divide meat mixture into six equal portions.
Press meat mixture around eggs with hands, keeping the oval shape.
Sprinkle eggs with flour, coating lightly on all sides.
Dip into beaten egg and then roll in bread crumbs. Heat vegetable oil in deep fat fryer or deep heavy saucepan to 350 degrees on deep fat thermometer.
Cook one egg at a time for about 4 - 5 minutes or until well browned.
Drain on paper toweling; cool, refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with chips.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: For cake, pour boiling water over oats. Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat margarine until creamy. Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oat mixture. Mix well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to the other mixture.
Mix well and pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in juices and rind. Pour in 1-quart mold.
(You may add mandarin oranges slices, drained, if desired.)
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ruth's lemon stuff
directions: Combine flour and butter; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.
In bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread in cooled crust.
Set aside.

title: sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Brown bacon in Dutch oven; add onions and cook until tender. Add potatoes, salt and pepper. Cover with sauerkraut and sausage. Add juniper berries and enough beer to cover potatoes. Simmer (covered) until tender (20 to 30 minutes). Serves 6 to 8.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until only tender in salted boiling water.
Mix brown sugar, water, butter and salt in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Add sweet potatoes, gently stirring until glazed and heated through.

title: my beef stew
directions: Note:
Read all directions before starting recipe.

title: dolly's fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Cook for 5 minutes. Mix in powdered sugar.
Spread into pan; let cool.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 475° oven until golden brown (about 30 minutes).
Can also be made into muffins.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a small bowl or jar and whisk or shake well.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Add self-rising flour and egg; mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon mixture over sugared peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli hot dish
directions: Place cooked, drained broccoli on bottom of pan.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Pour sauce made from soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice over the chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over the sauce to cover it.
Place bread crumbs mixed with butter over the cheese. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Core and quarter unpared apples, then slice in 1/4-inch slices. Heat fat in skillet and add apples.
Cover and cook slowly for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add sugar and cook until transparent and tender, lifting and turning with spatula until done.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Stir cake mix with pudding.
Add a few drops of green coloring, if desired.
Add water and oil to the mix.
Then add extract.
Add the eggs, one at a time, using low speed.
Beat 5 minutes.
Grease an angel food cake pan or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; then remove from pan.

title: saute of vegetable fermiere
directions: Trim and cut vegetables into very thin slices.
Rinse and drain mushrooms; dry and slice thinly.
Melt butter in skillet. Add carrots and turnips; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook, tossing and stirring, over high heat for about 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook, tossing and stirring, for about 2 minutes. Add the shallots and toss.
Cook briefly.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jennifer's generous ginger cookies
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Add sugar and beat another 2 minutes.
Sift flour over batter and fold in with rubber spatula.
Fold in cooled margarine.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain hamburg.
Add taco seasoning mix and water. Boil away.
Add rinsed and drained pinto beans, onion and green pepper.
Let mixture sit overnight.
Add shredded lettuce, tomatoes, crushed Doritos, Catalina dressing and cheese.
Mix well.

title: french bread(bread machine)
directions: Whip the whites until stiff and set aside.
Put ingredients in bread machine in the order required by your machine.
Start machine; after all ingredients are mixed, stop machine and add beaten egg whites.
(Note:
Use the dough cycle.)
When dough is ready to form into loaf, let rest for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle or mist with water and cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flu soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cover with water and let them start cooking good; add onion, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Season with Mazola, butter or meat grease.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes; if too thick, add tomato juice or water.
My mother's answer to chicken noodle soup when we had colds or flu.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and enough water to cover in 4-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook 25 minutes to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in mayonnaise, cream cheese and onion powder, salt and pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: darlene's easy fudgediagonal, iowa
directions: Stir butter, milk and sugar together on high until rolling boil.
Turn down to medium-high and cook to soft ball stage.

title: easy easy pecan pralines
directions: Lay wax paper on top of folded newspaper.
You will need two pieces about 12 to 18 inches long (the newspaper will help the pralines release after cooling).
Mix sugars, milk, butter and pecans in saucepan over medium high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil exactly 1 1/2 minutes and while continuing to stir. Remove from heat and stir for another 30 seconds.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture cools to the thickness of cream.
Immediately spoon out onto wax paper.
Allow to cool a few minutes.
May not be doubled.

title: chocolate kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and peanut butter until blended.
Add 1 cup sugar and then brown sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add both eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture until well combined.

title: best nut loaf
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Applesauce can replace oil in all recipes calling for oil or shortening.
Add to dry items; beat well and add nuts.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown the meat (adding no salt).
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Add more noodles on top the last 15 minutes.

title: christmas carol punch
directions: Core apples; slice into 1/2-inch rings.
In Dutch oven, combine cider, cinnamon, cloves, apple rings and raisins.
Bring to boil over high heat; reduce heat to low and simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until apples are just tender.
Remove cloves; add oranges, lemon slices and lemon juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Ladle into large mugs, including an apple ring, some raisins and citrus slices in each serving.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: party punch
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Mix strawberry Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice.
When ready to serve, add sherbet and 7-Up.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix water with soda; cool.
Cream shortening with sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift flour with salt.
Add creamed mixture alternately with cooled liquid.
Stir in cereals and buttermilk; put in covered container in refrigerator.
Can be used for weeks as needed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mixture improves after second day.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Peel potatoes and mash.
Add in eggs.
Add milk.
Add sugar to taste.
Add butter.
Add flour. Mix very well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Simmer carrots until barely tender.
Drain and add to salad dressing in large bowl.
Simmer broccoli about 8 minutes until not quite tender.
Add onion and green pepper; simmer 3 to 4 more minutes.
Drain and add to carrots.
Add mushrooms.
Stir to coat. Refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally to re-coat.
Should be tightly covered.
Tastes best if allowed to warm up slightly, not heated, just stand at room temperature for 1/2 hour or 1 hour before serving.

title: crackling bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add milk and egg; beat well. Add cracklings and pour into well-greased skillet or muffin tins. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan the pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine (melted).
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Beat together the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and add Cool Whip. Pour mixture over crumbs.
Mix strawberry jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Garnish with chopped walnuts.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening at high speed 10 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add one cup flour. Beat at a low speed one minute.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Beat well. Add flavoring. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased tube pan.

title: patrick's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until batter is smooth.
Pour each pancake into preheated electric frying pan at 325° lightly sprayed with Pam.
Turn over when bubbly, cook until golden.

title: coulibiac wreath
directions: Drain, bone and break salmon into chunks or flake.
Combine rice, 1/2 cup sour cream, 1/4 cup melted butter, lemon juice, dill and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in salmon.

title: strawberry-pineapple jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; put in complete package of frozen strawberries.
Add pineapple when strawberries melt.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice.

title: good cake
directions: Combine mix, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 3/4 cup oil, eggs and sour cream.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Place 1/3 of batter in well-greased pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 on batter in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar/cinnamon mix.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake in oven at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hummingbird pie
directions: Place margarine, almonds and coconut in skillet and brown lightly; set aside and let cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, milk and Cool Whip.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Combine almonds and butter in a 2-cup glass measure. Microwave, uncovered, at power level High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until almonds are lightly toasted.
Set aside.

title: frozen lemonade icebox pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours or until set.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and carrots in boiling, salted water until crisp tender.
Meanwhile, in saucepan saute the onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually add the milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Drain the cabbage and carrots.
Place half in a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the sauce; sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat the layers.
In a small skillet, melt the remaining butter.
Add the bread crumbs, marjoram and thyme; cook and stir until lightly browned.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cabbage is tender and top is browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: smoked salmon cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine cream cheese, Parmesan, hot sauce, lemon juice and pepper in food processor.
Cut smoked salmon into 32 small pieces and place a piece in each toast cup. Spoon about 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons of cheese mixture over salmon and top with dill.
Bake approximately 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mincemeat pies
directions: Mix with cider or fruit juice (about 1/2 gallon).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift together plain flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour mixture, one spoonful at a time, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla; stir.
Pour batter into well-greased pan(s).
Bake 1 hour at 325°, 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook frozen spinach as directed on package.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Prepare the day before.
Use as dip for vegetables.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Spread peanut butter on buttered surface about the size of a cookie sheet.
(Wooden table or countertop is best).

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar; add flour and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts and chopped apples.
Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Good with butterscotch chips distributed on cake before baking.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
I have used Egg Beaters in this recipe.

title: stuffed mushrooms(do ahead)
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with deviled ham.
Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Fill mushroom caps with cream cheese mixture.
Broil or bake until hot.
Can be made and and heated at the last minute.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: sis vera's canned green beans
directions: Put vinegar, water, and salt in large boiler.
Bring to boil. Add your home grown green beans and boil for 12 - 15 minutes. Pack your jars and seal.
When ready to serve, drain beans, season and cook.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a 10 x 15-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill and spread on top of crescent rolls.
Top with whatever veggies you like.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 5 or 6-quart pan over medium-high heat, cook onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in oil until vegetables are soft and just beginning to brown (10 minutes).
Stir in paprika and cook for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes (break up with spoon) and their liquid, water, salt, pepper, Tabasco and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp and continue simmering until shrimp turn pink (6 to 8 minutes). Stir cornstarch mixture and add to pan.
Cook, stirring, until sauce bubbles and thickens slightly.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve in bowls over hot, cooked rice.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix for one minute.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a jelly roll pan ready.
Mix butter and Worcestershire sauce in a large bowl.
Add pecans and toss to coat.
Spread on ungreased pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until toasted.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: beef salad(yum nyun)
directions: Bake meat in oven until cooked (350°).
Slice the cooked meat into bite-size.
Slice the vegetables into bite-size.
Mix meat and vegetables together.
Squeeze 1/4 lemon into the mix.
Crush the peppers and add
to the mix.
Add fish sauce and sugar.

title: nano's hot potato salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs and let cool.
Chop eggs, onion and celery. Prepare instant potatoes according to directions for 4 servings. Stir in eggs, onion, celery, relish, mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tacos
directions: Saute hamburger until pink is gone.
Boil potatoes.
Grate cheese, tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Add cumin seed.
Mix all together.
Put into tortilla and double over.
Fry in grease.
Let drain.
When ready to eat, sprinkle grated cheese, diced tomato and lettuce into tortilla.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and brush with oleo.
Return to oven and bake another 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients.
Place meat mixture into oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 - 60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fudge cake with icing
directions: In oblong baking pan, mix flour and 2 cups sugar.
Heat 1 stick
margarine,
water
and
oil until boiling.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix well by hand.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture. Add eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes;
set aside.

title: beefy tomato rice soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in large saucepan.
Drain grease.
Add water, beef bouillon, tomatoes and spice to taste.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer one hour.
Stir in carrots, celery and rice during the last 30 minutes of cooking time.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, flour, spices and yellows of eggs.
Beat egg whites
and add last. Fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325°. Test by putting knife in pie to see if done.

title: salmon soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, potatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add salmon after pulling skin off and deboning.
Add dill weed.
In small bowl, combine milk and cornstarch; blend with wire whisk until smooth.
Slowly stir in soup.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cook an additional 2 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If you like more salmon, you can use two cans. Pour salmon juice in pot with potatoes and cook along in soup.

title: green bean and mozzarella salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: norway fudge
directions: Boil sugars together with cream until mixture forms a very soft ball when tested in cold water, then add butter, vanilla and nuts.
(May use other kinds of nuts instead of black walnuts.) Let stand until cool, then beat until light brown.
May be put in buttered flat dish as for fudge or formed into rolls for slicing. Keep in covered dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly.
Mix with soup, mayonnaise and onion to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Add layer of cheese, then crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over top of casserole dish. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double boiler or in a crock-pot on low heat (2 hours).
Heat, stirring occasionally, until all cheese is melted and bubbly hot.
Serve while hot with plain corn chips, raw cauliflower, etc.
Have plenty tea and soda to cool down the throat.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cut pork in small strips and saute in 2 tablespoons oil with ham.
Add onion, green pepper and parsley.
Cook until tender. Add remaining oil, rice, bean sprouts, salt and pepper; stir until well mixed.
Make a well in the center of rice mixture.
Add eggs and cook until semi-solid, then stir into rice and cook until done.
Good with pepper steak.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: jewish rice
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Mix all other ingredients (uncooked rice).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apple slices in ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Put blueberries on top of apple slices.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oats, margarine, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake until topping is light brown and blueberries are hot, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until ready to serve.
Serve over individual plates of layered Frito corn chips.
Top with grated cheese, lettuce, chopped onions, green peppers, and/or jalapenos.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place all ingredients (except spices, tomato sauce and whiskey) into crock-pot.
Mix spices, tomato sauce and whiskey together and pour these into the pot.
Extra water and potatoes may be added to fill the pot or change consistency.
Cover.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Then on low for 4 hours; stir periodically.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine Crisco, margarine and sugar. Mix well; add eggs and vanilla. Set aside a mixture of the dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking powder and soda). It is a good idea to add the nuts to the dry ingredients to coat. This keeps them from settling to the bottom of the baking pan. Add the milk and dry ingredients alternately into the egg mixture. Pour into a greased and floured angel food pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute vegetables in skillet with butter for 10 minutes. Add flour
to vegetables, stirring for 1 minute.
Mix chicken broth and
milk together; add to skillet mixture.
Cook until thick. Add
salt
and pepper.
Add chicken.
Put pie crust on top and bake at 400° until brown.

title: pea casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; put in casserole dish.
Add peas and tomato soup.
Put mashed potatoes on top and brown in oven.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter, powered sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt. Add to creamed mixture, then add nuts.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
May be placed very close together on cookie sheet. They will not spread out.
When cooled, roll in powdered sugar.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix soup with milk; stir constantly while heating.
Do not boil.
Add broccoli, pepper to taste and butter.
Heat and serve.

title: fr. wilbert's original new york style cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with butter, then dust with 1/4 cup crushed graham cracker crumbs. Place spring-form pan in freezer to chill.

title: chocolate mints
directions: Melt all together in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Drop small dabs on wax paper.
Allow to set.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: In a bowl beat eggs.
Add soup, mayonnaise, pecans and onion. Stir in broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: quicky chilli(fast, cheap, easy)
directions: Water can be added if it is too thick.

title: microwave candy pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except baking soda, in 8-cup glass measure.
Cook on High 12 minutes, stirring at 4 minute intervals. Stir in baking soda.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Beat and drop by spoonfuls onto greased waxed paper.

title: scandinavian almond bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in egg and extract.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Divide dough into fourths; roll into 12x3 inch rectangles 5 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Brush with milk; sprinkle with almonds.

title: easy country cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish; mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl.
Pour fruit into butter; pour flour mixture over fruit.
Place in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut lemons into thin slices.
Remove seeds.
Place in bowl and sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Then press fruit with a potato masher to extract juice.
Add water, pressing fruit until well flavored.
Serve over ice cubes.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: lite spinach-bacon deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks into a small mixing bowl and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sand tarts viennese crescents
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add other ingredients. Shape as desired. Bake for 25 minutes at 300°. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine beef, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place potatoes in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with onions.
Cover with beef.
Spoon pork and beans over beef, then pour on tomato soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 X 10 X 1 inch baking pan.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, sugar, margarine and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press crumb mixture firmly and evenly into baking pan.

title: heath brickle blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add both sugars and cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in Heath Brickle.
Spread over bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until done, about 30 minutes. When cool, cut into bars (3 x 1-inches).

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, mix well. Batter will be stiff.
Pour 3/4 batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; spread.
Add pie filling, spread over batter.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoon on fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar (optional).
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Check after 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Soak overnight in 4 times their volume of water.
Drain.
Cover with water, and bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer, add other ingredients.
Cook until beans are tender. Add more water if needed.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange wedges, peel side down, in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Brush occasionally with remaining oil mixture.

title: zucchini-barley casserole
directions: Add barley to boiling salt water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook vegetables in oil until tender.
Combine with barley. Top with cheese.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Put milk in pan over low heat.
Heat until hot.
With heat still low, mix sugar and flour in bowl.
Mix egg and vanilla in bowl.
Slowly mix into hot milk until desired thickness.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crumble crackers and mix with nuts and half the sugar. Beat egg whites until stiff and add to the remaining sugar. Pour egg whites into dry ingredients; add vanilla. Mix well and pour into a buttered pie plate. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Allow pie to cool. Beat whipping cream and 1 teaspoon sugar. When stiff, pour over top of pie.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Mix all the rest of ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in pan and top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and potato bake
directions: Grease cake pan and arrange chicken pieces in bottom.
Pour peas on top.
In mixing bowl, combine all soups.
Pour over chicken and peas.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45-60 minutes until meat is tender.
Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Arrange potatoes on your plate and top with chicken.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat; beat in sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Remember to keep this frosting chilled between servings.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups frosting.

title: homemade cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine cinnamon with applesauce to form a stiff dough.
If necessary, add additional applesauce.
Roll out the dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters and make a hole for a ribbon.
Carefully place the ornaments on a wire rack to dry. They should air dry for several days.
Turn them over occasionally to dry completely.
Makes about 12 ornaments.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least one hour before serving.

title: california apricot fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve as a salad or arrange on wooden skewers as a fruit kabob.
Yield:
5 servings; 0 cholesterol.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; blend well and add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: easy chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pan you will use for baking chicken.
Dip chicken in melted margarine so both sides are buttered.
Lay aside. Add rice to margarine in pan.
Combine 2 soups and water; add to rice mixture.
Salt and pepper (sparingly) chicken and arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or 425° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs until light.
Add applesauce, mixing well.
Blend in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices to mixture alternately with water.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion and parsley.
Add the jar of sauce to the meat. Add the oregano, marjoram, thyme, basil, bay leaf, red pepper and minced garlic to the sauce.
Simmer the sauce for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch or oblong Pyrex 2-quart dish, smooth the cherry pie filling, then pineapple on top of that, then sprinkle sugar.
Smooth dry cake mix on top of that, then pour melted margarine, then chopped pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.
It is delicious!

title: mock sour cream
directions: Mix and let stand until cool.
Use as regular sour cream. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli buds, discarding large stems.
Peel and slice onion.
Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in large bowl. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in small bowl; add to broccoli mixture.
Marinate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: "pecan crispies"
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Sprinkle bottom of pan with Doritos.
Pour combined mixture over Doritos.
Sprinkle more Doritos over mixture.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray baking dish with Pam. Pour in tuna mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion and green peppers.
Drain grease from pan; add rice and mix.
Add garlic salt, cumin, salt and pepper and mix well.
Dice the whole tomatoes and mix.
Stir until all is hot and serve.

title: mom's mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, quarter and boil potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then combine the butter and cream in a mixer.
Add hot potatoes and mix. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mrs. taylor's pickles
directions: Note:
This recipe makes great crispy sweet pickles and is worth the work, but once begun, it must be carried through on schedule.
Plan your time carefully in advance.

title: kansas taco sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients except lemon juice to a boil in large saucepan; simmer until mixture is desired consistency.
(Blend in food processor, coarse.)
Pour into clean sterilized jars, adding lemon juice 1 Tbsp./pint, 2 Tbsp./quart to each jar.
Stir gently, seal jars.

title: english cookies
directions: Add water to raisins; cook 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add coffee and vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Flour cooled raisins lightly and add to mixture.
Spread batter on greased cookie sheet with edges.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread with thin icing made with powdered sugar and water.
Cut into squares.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix sugar and strawberry Jell-O together and pour in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rhubarb on top of Jell-O mixture.
Add marshmallows on top of rhubarb.
Prepare cake mix as shown on box and pour over mixture.
Bake it all as directed on cake mix box.

title: chicken thighs mozzarella
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip each thigh in egg, drain and dredge in flour mixture.
Heat oil in 4 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add coated thighs and cook for 2 minutes on each side, until brown.
Remove thighs with slotted spoon and arrange in single layer in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter to skillet and saute mushrooms for 4 minutes.
Cut each slice of ham in half and place on each thigh.
Scatter mushrooms over all and top with Mozzarella.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions and set aside (to thicken).
In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, oil, baking powder and pudding.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cake mixture in pan. Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together in a big bowl.
Add dressing.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds.
Set aside to cool.
Cream margarine with sugar; add buttermilk, Bran Buds and eggs. Separately sift 5 cups flour with baking soda and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with 4 cups of all-bran.
Combine with wet ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator in a large covered bowl until ready to bake.
Do not stir batter with spoon before putting in greased muffin tins.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 minutes. Mixture will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: eggplant casserole(meatless)
directions: Brown eggplant in olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Drain on paper towels.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer eggplant, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese (3 layers).
Top with bread crumbs, oregano and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: rotel chicken
directions: In a long pan, crush Doritos in bottom.
Boil your chicken and pull from bone.
Layer chicken on top of Doritos.
Then layer diced onion (in a bowl mix Ro-Tel and soup), 1 layer soup mixture on top of onion, then add cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: confetti pea salad
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients and warm until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over the remaining ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Drain.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Blend.
Add flour, coconut, cocoa, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
As soon as it's removed from the oven, cover with a 9-ounce jar of marshmallow cream.

title: enchiladas(low-fat)
directions: Cook meat in skillet with spices until brown (done); get tomato juice hot.
Dip tortillas in hot tomato juice.
Put hot tortilla in pan you are going to cook them in; place 1 tablespoon meat and 1/2 diced cheese on tortilla and roll up.
Continue until you have all 12 tortillas rolled up side by side.
Pour remaining tomato juice on top and bake until cheese is melted.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch pan. Serve with chopped onion.

title: garbage bread
directions: Stretch dough, put in ingredients.
Seal edges (prick it). Cover to raise.
Cook.
Watch until brown at 400°.

title: pineapple beat cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add pineapple, including juice.
Add flour, sugars and soda.
Add 1/2 of the nuts, saving the rest to sprinkle on top of the frosting.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: fudge with graham bottom
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the graham crumbs and sugar.
Mix. Spread on a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Flatten mixture into pan very well.
Melt the chips and stir in the peanut butter.
Pour over the crumb mixture and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours.
Makes about 50 bite size bites.

title: hungarian potatoes
directions: In greased casserole dish, grate potatoes, onion, carrots and cheese.
Pour in soup and milk.
Mix together well. Dot top with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (uncovered).

title: grits for fish fry
directions: Spray Pam into pot.
Cook green pepper and onion in bacon fat until tender but not browned.
Add water and salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and add grits, pimiento and cheese and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in butter and bacon.
Remove from heat and serve when thickened.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Stir together.
Serve warm.
Garnish with lettuce, chives and olives.
Serve with plenty of tortilla chips.

title: country garden salad dressing
directions: Blend in blender. Keep refrigerated. Makes approximately 20 ounces. If it should separate, just mix well again.
Makes a sweet and sour dressing.

title: chewy cheese
directions: Place cheese (either processed cheese slices or slices of Cheddar) between 2 slices of bread.
Heat a frying pan over medium heat.
Place the sandwiches on the pan, butter side down; cook 2 to 3 minutes, until golden brown.
Turn sandwich with lifter and repeat for the other side.
Remove from pan.
Cut into quarters and serve with crunchy pickles.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Add all ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into bowl and sit in freezer until solid, but not frozen. Spread layer of sour cream over jello and then pour rest of jello mixture over the sour cream.
Let sit in freezer until solid, but not frozen.
Remove and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter,	butter or margarine and vanilla in a large bowl; beat with electric beater until well blended. Beat in sugar until light and
fluffy;
beat
in eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour
and salt just until well blended; spread batter in a greased 13 x
x	2-inch	baking	pan.
Bake
in moderate
oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until center springs back
when
lightly touched
with fingertip.
Remove pan from oven to wire rack; cool slightly.
Combine sugar with water in a
small
bowl;
stir until smooth.
Drizzle from a spoon over still
warm
cookies in pan. Swirl with bowl of spoon to make random pattern.
Melt chocolate with shortening over simmering water
in
top of double boiler. Drizzle over the white glaze for
a
black	and
white
pattern. When
cool, using a sharp knife, cut into 36 rectangles. Carefully lift out of pan with spatula.

title: rhubarb crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and top with a mixture of the last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: just plain pot roast
directions: Trim meat (optional).
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper. Brown in Wesson oil in Dutch oven.
Add water; cover and then add vegetables.
Pour Hunt's sauce over everything and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
You might need to add more water.

title: barley and pine nut casserole
directions: Rinse and drain barley.
Toast pine nuts in 1 tablespoon melted butter in skillet.
Remove nuts and set aside.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter to the pan.
Saute barley and onion until barely toasted.
Stir in chives, parsley, salt and pepper. Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add hot stock; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry on both sides until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chicken divan
directions: Wash and dry tuna.
Cut off any skin and the dark meat (will be considerably darker than the rest of the tuna).
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and stir together.
In a flat container, coat both sides of tuna generously with all the marinade; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hearty man baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Cover with bacon strips and bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and cold water.
To this, add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let jell.

title: mother's chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
(I put mine in the blender.)
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the center of pie stops shaking.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
and form into bite-size balls.
Then dip in chocolate mixture, 1 large package (12 ounces) chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin melted together in a saucepan.

title: sausage in rum sauce
directions: Cut each sausage into 3 pieces.
Brown sausages and drain well. Combine rest of ingredients and heat until sugar melts.
Place sausages in sauce.
Place in chafing dish or fondue pot to keep warm.
Have toothpicks handy and let everyone spear their own.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Press out cans of dinner rolls on ungreased jelly roll pan. Bake until golden brown.
Top with sour cream dip and fresh vegetables.

title: fantastic fried corn
directions: Place corn in a large skillet; turn on medium heat.
Add butter, whipping cream, sugar and salt.
Stirring constantly, heat until most of the whipping cream and butter is absorbed into the corn.

title: cornbread dressing holiday special(serves 12)
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients.
No special order.
Cook approximately 2 1/2 hours at 300°, stirring once. Important: No stock from chicken or turkey.
No poultry fat! Oysters (1 pint) may be substituted for giblets.
Remove bay leaves at the time you stir (approximately 1 hour after cooking time).

title: baked fish
directions: Oil pan, salt fish and rub fish with oil.
Bake about 30 minutes or until fish stops running water at 400°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, raisins and nuts or coconut.
Mix eggs and oil together.
Add egg and oil mixture to flour and stir until just moistened.

title: creme de menthe chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring water, Crisco, butter and cocoa to a boil. Combine flour and sugar and pour hot mixture over this and mix well. Add baking soda, salt, vanilla, creme de menthe, buttermilk and eggs. Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 40 minutes or until it tests done with a toothpick.

title: yummy bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Stir in rice crispies.
Divide mixture in half.
Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press it down.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic in Crisco.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and seasoning. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Alternate cooked noodles, cheese, cottage cheese and meat. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: beef choufleur
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch squares and brown about 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir to lightly coat vegetables with soy sauce.
Cover pan and simmer until vegetables are barely tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and broth.
Add to meat mixture with green onions.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated and sauce is thick. Serve over rice.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Refrigerate overnight. This is an excellent dressing for spinach salad.
It can be used hot or cold. To heat, place in microwave until warm.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the yeast and hot water.
Add the sugar, eggs, salt and warm water.
Mix with the flour; let rise until double.
Roll out. Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon until oleo is soaked up.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While still hot, spread with butter frosting.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Stir in brown sugar. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup; cut slices in half. Arrange atop sugar, placing a cherry half in each hollow. Place shortening in mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and reserved pineapple syrup; mix until flour is moistened. Beat vigorously 2 minutes. Pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes; invert on plate. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: prune bread
directions: Combine prunes and water in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain prunes, reserving 2 cups liquid. Combine prunes, reserved liquid, sugar, lard, spices and salt in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until lard melts.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: red pepper salsa
directions: Cut red peppers and chile in half lengthwise.
Remove and discard seeds and membrane.
Place peppers, skin side up, on baking sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat for 15 minutes or until peppers are charred.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 1/2 cup sugar, pineapple and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese (softened at room temperature) with 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring well.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Spread pineapple mixture over bottom of the pie shell.
Pour cream cheese mixture over pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue to bake for 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup potato chips.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crumbled potato chips on top.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: turkey souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water; add cold water, mayonnaise, vinegar, onion and pepper.
Beat until well blended. Pour into an 8-inch square pan; freeze 15 to 20 minutes or until firm, about 1-inch from edge but soft in center.
Spoon mixture into bowl and whip until fluffy; fold in turkey and chopped vegetables.
Pour into a 4-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill in refrigerator until firm, 30 to 60 minutes; unmold.
Garnish with salad greens and serve with additional mayonnaise, if desired. Makes about 4 cups or 4 entree servings.

title: sno-ball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice, pineapple and juice.
Chill until partly firm.
Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip (as directed on package).
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Line large bowl with aluminum foil.
Break cake into pieces; add layer for layer of angel food cake and gelatin mixture.
Chill overnight.
Remove from bowl by laying plate on top.
Turn upside-down.
Mix other package of Dream Whip and spread over cake.
Put coconut all over the cake. Top with red or green maraschino cherries cut in half.
May also use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice and cold water to measure 1 2/3 cups liquid.
Add to jello; chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in nuts, celery, cranberry sauce and pineapple. Chill.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sand cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies.

title: easy bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk, eggs and oil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy george washington cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over butter. Spoon in cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until top is golden.

title: next best thing to robert redford cake
directions: Mix and spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: You will need 1 package cupcakes.

title: melba's green beans
directions: Saute onion and bacon; pour off grease.
Mix other ingredients; add to onion and bacon.
Stir until thick.
Pour over green beans and stir.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and lemonade together until smooth.
Spoon fruit into individual serving bowls and top with cream cheese mixture.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 9-inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare pie crust according to directions.
Place bottom crust over pecan mixture in pan.
In large bowl, mix apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with second crust and flute top; cut several slits (only in top shell).
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then turn upside-down on serving place.
Good with ice cream.

title: mexican fudge(appetizer)
directions: Combine cheeses; spread 1/2 in the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat the eggs; mix with taco or enchilada sauce. Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Spread remaining cheese on top; bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until eggs are set and cheese is golden.
Remove from oven; cool slightly so eggs and cheese are firm enough to slice.
Cut into 1-inch squares; serve squares on corn chips as appetizers.
Can be served as a main dish by cutting into 4 to 6-inch squares and eliminating corn chips. Makes 81 appetizer servings.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute okra in shortening for 10 minutes or until okra appears dry, stirring constantly.
Add onion, garlic, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves and add liquid hot pepper sauce.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugars, vanilla, corn syrup, baking soda, margarine peanut butter and oats together.

Stir in M&M's and chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly. Bake about 10 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven while cookies are still a little moist. Do not overbake! (No flour.) Enjoy!!

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in blender.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add cranberries.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Fry sausage until crisp.
Drain well.
