Slice or crumble cheese and melt with water in a double broiler.
Mix well with Bisquick and crumbled sausage.
Roll in small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake sausage balls for about 25 minutes.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine sour cream and next 6 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir well.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Let cake cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.

title: coconut dream squares
directions: Combine 1
cup	flour
and
cup
brown sugar.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
Press firmly into a 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs until thick. Gradually add 1 cup brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy. Mix
1/4 cup flour with baking powder.
Fold into egg mixture. Add
coconut
and
nuts.
Spread
over
baked crust. Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hamburger and pea casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, season.
Layer in casserole: hamburger, peas, rice, cottage cheese, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Fill two ice trays with 7-Up and freeze.
Empty frozen 7-Up into punch bowl.
Add fruit juices and remaining 7-Up.
Mix and serve.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Pour off juice and thicken with beaten eggs, cornstarch and sugar, then cook like a pudding.
Cool, then add pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
cheese.
Pour
half
of batter into
greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 of cheese over batter.
Add remaining batter.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Grease pan. Pour corn bread mixture into pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on top at 350 degrees.

title: western barbecue sauce
directions: Add brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire to the all-purpose sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place chicken or ribs in baking pan. Brush meat with the Wesson oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Drain fat and turn meat. Spoon barbecue sauce over and bake 30 to 45 minutes or until tender, turning and basting with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: morning biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift dry ingredients. Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or your hands until the mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Make a well in the middle of the mixture and pour in buttermilk. Mix just until ingredients are combined and a soft dough is formed. Do not overmix. On a lightly floured surface, knead the dough gently until it is soft and elastic (not sticky). Pat dough out until about 1/2-inch thick. Cut circles with a cookie cutter or drinking glass. Place the biscuits 1/2-inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet for a crisp-crusted biscuit or touching each other for a softer biscuit. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt,
baking
powder
and
wheat germ; add
shortening,
milk
and
egg.
Be
careful
not
to overbeat this batter.
Mix into
another
bowl,
brown
sugar, cinnamon, flour, nuts and wheat germ.
Next,	cut into the dry ingredients the butter.
Pour 1/2 batter into a square greased cake pan.
Top with 1/2 dry mixture,
then pour the other half of batter and then top with the
rest of dry mixture.	Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: beefy-cheese ball
directions: Lay out cream cheese to soften.
Chop onions and mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: When cake cools, cut in 4 horizontal layers. Mix sugar, vanilla and sour cream. Stir in Cool Whip. Fold in 1 large package coconut. Ice the cake between each layer to make 4 layers. Sprinkle the other large package coconut on top and sides of cake. Refrigerate. Cake gets more moist after 2 days in fridge.

title: maude's barbecue
directions: *I use my zucchini relish or you can chop 1 green pepper and 2 cups celery and cook with onions.

title: chocolate crumb crust
directions: Work crumbs and butter together until crumbs are doughy. Press crumb mixture evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients. Sift together the remaining ingredients. Mix all of the above ingredients. Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Dip tops in sugar. Place sugar side up 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle each cookie with 2 to 3 drops of water to produce a cracked surface. Bake just until set, but not hard. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place rice in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soups and water and pour over rice.
Arrange cut up fryer on top of rice.
Season chicken with salt and pepper lightly.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with biscuits and stewed or fried apples.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: crab imperial(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mustard; heat and stir until smooth and bubbly.
Slowly add half and half; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add green pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in crabmeat; pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve on toast points.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Pour butter all around top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion in melted shortening.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, then add kidney beans.
Pour meat mixture into a greased 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with corn bread mixture, spreading with a wet knife.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 minutes.

title: 5 pound fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in large pan.
Bring to a boil. Boil 6 minutes (soft ball stage).
Remove and add vanilla.
Have chips, nuts and marshmallows in large bowl.
Pour cooked ingredients over this and stir until well mixed.
Pour into large buttered jelly roll pan.
Let sit overnight or 12 hours.
Cut and spread out to air and dry on wax paper.
Makes a nice large holiday batch.

title: apple-nut squares
directions: Mix eggs, sugars, oil
and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir everything together. Add apples
and nuts.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: holiday cheese treat
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail thoroughly and dice.
Combine cream cheese, fruit cocktail, pudding, orange extract and orange juice. Roll into a ball.
Roll in the slivered almonds.
Refrigerate about two hours.
Serve with crackers.
Suggestion:
Wheat Thins.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, except egg whites.
Whip egg whites and fold in mixture.
Pour in pie crusts and bake at 350° until brown (30 minutes).

title: carrot applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl mix the dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl beat
eggs.
Stir
in oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add applesauce
and carrots.
Mix well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Fold
in
raisins
and
half of nuts.
Pour batter in greased
pan.
Sprinkle
on
the
rest of the nuts. Bake at 350° in
a
tube
pan for 65 minutes or in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes or makes about 35 cupcakes (bake for 20 to 25 minutes).

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
When mixed well, add margarine and pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes and stir and cook for 12 more minutes.
Then you may add 1 cup of raisins after it has baked.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan and saute until tender broccoli, onion and carrots.
Stir in milk, soup or broth and seasoning. Cover and simmer on medium low (heat) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 5.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Melt margarine.
Dip breasts in margarine and roll in Ritz crackers.
Bake in 350° oven until tender (about one hour).
I usually bake mine in an iron skillet.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: honey spice glaze chicken
directions: Combine Heinz 57 sauce and honey. Brush chicken with melted butter. Brush on honey and sauce mix. Grill or broil until chicken is cooked, turning and brushing frequently.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Break eggs into mixer bowl and add brown sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
While eggs are beating, sift flour, measure and add salt.
Dip gumdrops into flour and snip with scissors. Continue dipping and snipping until all are cut in small pieces into the flour.
Stir this mixture into egg mixture and stir until all flour disappears.
Add nuts and spread into well greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut in squares with a wet knife.

title: sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into metal trays.
When frozen, slice and enjoy.
May have to stand to soften to eat. Gets very hard.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Bake in 2 round cake pans. Cool overnight.

title: fettucine agli olio
directions: Warm olive oil at low heat.
Add crushed garlic.
Do not let the olive oil overheat, as this will take the flavor out of the garlic.
Cook fettucine in boiling water for about 10 minutes, or until tender.
Drain fettucine; place in a large bowl with the garlic and olive oil.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cooked apples
directions: Place apples in saucepan.
Add margarine and sugar.
Bring to a simmer and cook for about 45 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: candy cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a pan on the stove.
Stir, then bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Then add the last 3 ingredients. Stir, then drop by the teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Enjoy.

title: dixie crossroads corn fritters
directions: Heat oil to approximately 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine eggs, milk and butter blend.
Fold egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Add corn last.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil; deep fry about 5 minutes or until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cornbread cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and milk in a large bowl; stir well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in eggs, salt and garlic powder.

title: chili rellenos squares
directions: Butter 8-inch square dish.
Mix cheeses together.
Layer with cheese, green chilies (sliced lengthwise); repeat layers.
Mix eggs, milk and flour; pour over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with cayenne pepper, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, clams, clam broth and onion.
Mix well.
Pile into bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.

title: wacky cake(a.k.a. three hole cake)
directions: Into an ungreased 8-inch square pan, sift and mix the flour, soda and salt.
Mix cocoa and sugar together and add to pan.
Stir all to mix well.
Make three holes in dry mixture.
Pour vinegar in first hole; oil in second hole; vanilla in third hole.
Pour cold water over all.
Stir or use rotary beater until mixed thoroughly and smooth.
Bang on table three times.
Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese pups(adaptation from a pillsbury bake-off recipe)
directions: You will need an electric skillet set at 325° to 350°.
Makes 16 "pups."

title: chicken divan
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends of lower stalks; wash broccoli thoroughly.
Divide into equal size spears, trimming stalks as necessary.
Pour water into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange broccoli with flowerets facing center of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes, or until broccoli is tender, giving dish a half turn after 4 minutes.
Drain.
Rearrange broccoli in dish so flowerets face outside.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter with powdered sugar and 1 cup granulated sugar. Beat in eggs until smooth and creamy.
Slowly stir in oil, vanilla, baking soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.
Chill dough.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place on baking sheet; press down gently with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add soup, water and rice.
Chop cabbage.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Pour hamburger mixture over.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Beat eggs and scramble in a lightly oiled or buttered skillet. While eggs are still runny, add meat of your choice and finish cooking.
Remove from heat.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add all except fruit (will be thick).
Add apples.
Sprinkle top with butterscotch bits.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Chill overnight.

title: little venice spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in nonstick pot; add paste and fry paste approximately 3 to 5 minutes.
In a blender, puree tomatoes 1 can at a time.
Add fried paste.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 45 to 60 minutes over a medium-low heat.
You may add meatballs or other meat with other ingredients.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.
This sauce is very low in fat.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Mix cream

cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs together. Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of foil baking cups (foil cups can be placed in muffin tins to cook). Pour mixture on top of vanilla wafer, about 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 320° for 20 minutes. Refrigerate to set cheese cake. Add 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling. Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: herb crusted beef roast
directions: Stir together garlic, oil, basil and pepper and brush even over meat.
Place roast fat side up on rack in shallow baking pan. Insert thermometer in thickest part.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
With fingers, crumble bread to make 1 cup crumbs.
Combine with parsley, onions and butter.
Remove roast; quickly pat crumb mixture over meat.
Return to oven; roast until thermometer is 135° (rare) to 155° (medium).
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes before carving.

title: best chocolate icing you'll ever eat!
directions: Bring to a boil and keep boiling for 2 to 3 minutes. Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and remove from stove; cool to lukewarm. (Put in the refrigerator for a few minutes to speed cooling.) After cooling, use mixer to beat to your preferred consistency. Then pour over your cake or brownies.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Makes 3 holes. Put vanilla in a hole, oil in a hole and vinegar in a hole.
Add 2 cups of water over top and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into two graham cracker crusts. Chill for 24 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in airtight container. Add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls to 1 cup hot water.

title: ham and pecan stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; cut ham into bite size strips.
Cut green pepper into 1-inch pieces.
In a small bowl, stir together reserved pineapple juice, soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch and red pepper.
Set the mixture aside.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add garlic, onion, celery and parsley.
Cook until soft.
Stir in tomato paste and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer slowly 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more until macaroni is tender.
Makes 8 servings.
Can serve with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: snicker doodles(cookies)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Stir into shortening mixture. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix thinly sliced cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with ice.
Let stand until ice is almost melted.
Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: homemade dumpling soup
directions: Cook together 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 22-minute cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Put flour and sugar in large bowl.
In a pan, bring to boil butter, water, shortening and cocoa.
Add to flour mixture.
Add milk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in greased cookie sheet and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in slow cooker in order given.
Cover and cook about 8 hours.
Stir mixture and serve on hamburger buns.

title: baked mac and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	as
directed
and drain. Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour. Stir in milk slowly and cook, stirring constantly,
until	mixture thickens. Add seasonings and
cheese, stirring
until
cheese
melts. Add macaroni and transfer to a buttered 1-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over macaroni. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Line crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan, not overlapping each other.
Mix brown sugar and butter.
Spoon over graham crackers. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.
Break into squares.

title: alberta's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until set in center.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice together; add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Gently stir in cherry pie filling.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Pound and flour steak pieces and brown in shortening.
Remove steak and put in large glass baking dish.
In skillet with meat drippings, add vegetables, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Thicken vegetable combination with 1 tablespoon flour in 1/4 cup water.
Cover steak pieces and bake.
Cover with shredded cheese during last 15 minutes of cooking time if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let cool to desired temperature and serve.

title: layered taco appetizer
directions: Layer ingredients on 12-inch pizza pan in order listed.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a prepared 9-inch pie shell. Cover with pecans. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in bowl.
Add apples, mix lightly.
Heap in pastry shell, 9-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and flute edges.
Cut vents.
Bake in 425° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, until crust is browned and apples are tender.
Cool on rack.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: whole wheat buns
directions: Mix warm water, oil, sugar or honey and yeast and rest for 15 minutes.
Add salt, eggs and whole wheat flour.
Shape immediately into rolls, cinnamon rolls or hamburger buns.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: day before payday cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in ungreased pan.
Make 3 holes in mix in pan.
Pour vanilla, vinegar and butter in holes.
Pour water over mix and stir.
Bake at 350° until done in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: kiwi cream tart
directions: Cool tart shell.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Let gelatin soften.
Heat until dissolved.
Stir in sour cream, sugar, flavoring and salt.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool, stirring occasionally.
When cooled and slightly thickened, whip cream and fold into mixture. Spoon into prepared tart shell, smooth top.
Refrigerate until set.
Peel fruit.
Cut lengthwise into thin slices.
Arrange on top and garnish with grapes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayo, soup, eggs and cheese.
Saute onion in margarine. Layer in casserole dish broccoli, onion, crumbs and soup; repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a gallon glass
jar.
Mix the vinegar and other ingredients.
Pour the vinegar mixture over cucumbers. Refrigerate.
Ready to eat after 1 week.

title: pork chops with vegetables
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Coat Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add chops. Brown on both sides.
Add savory, bay leaf, tomato juice and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover and cook 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 6 servings. Double for a crowd.

title: hot pineapple
directions: Mix and put into casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers on top. Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine on top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 375°.

title: heart healthy apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg substitute, oil and vanilla; add apples. Combine flour, soda, salt as desired and cinnamon; add to mixture. Add nuts and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Use buttermilk in mix instead of suggested liquid.
Bake in 3 layers, or bake in 2 layers and split them to make 4.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Brush 9 x 13-inch baking pan with soft butter.
Cover bottom with brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on sugar mixture.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, add sugar gradually continuing the creaming.
Add eggs, mix well.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter over arranged fruit, taking care to spread evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 40 minutes. Turn out at once upside down on cake plate.

title: never fail chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cornmeal, salt and butter.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Blend well before pouring into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Soak shrimp in ice water for 20 minutes; drain.
Heat soup and cream cheese until melted.
Add gelatine and 1/4 cup of water. Put back on heat and blend.
Let mixture cool.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate for several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: broken glass jello salad
directions: Prepare the raspberry jello, orange jello and lime jello using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour into 8-inch pans and chill until very firm. Cut each into squares. Dissolve the lemon jello and the sugar in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thick. Blend in the Cool Whip.
Fold in the jello cubes. Carefully pour into a
mold or a large glass bowl. Chill.

title: jam cake
directions: Use your preferred method for mixing cake.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Drain peppers.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar together.
Add mangoes and onions.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes after mixture begins to boil, then can.
I use this in my barbecue.
(I don't usually have yellow mangoes, so use 18 red and 18 green.)

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Press evenly in a 1 1/2-quart (8 x 4-inch) loaf dish, cook, covered with wax paper, 10 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
If desired, top with catsup or barbecue sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple beer muffins(like homemade yeast bread)
directions: Mix to a thick dough.
Spray a muffin pan with Pam.
Fill cup a little over half full.
Cook until a golden brown at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with butter.
You may not use all of beer.

title: jam thumbprints
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour, mixing well. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites, then roll in chopped walnuts.
Place 1-inch apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Press down center on each with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Just before serving, place jam in center of cookie.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: country corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into pie dish. Microwave on 70% power 8 to 9 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cover with foil and let stand 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In saucepan, mix together soup, water and half of the dry onion soup mix.
In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, egg and other half of the onion soup mix.
Shape mixture into small balls and drop into mushroom soup mixture.
Cook slowly 40 minutes.

title: cinna-meringue rhubarb pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add cream, rhubarb and butter. Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, melted butter and vanilla. Put in a dish.
Mix brown sugar, soft butter, flour and pecans. Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: chicken ratatouille or (what's-it-to-ya)
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook onions and garlic in olive oil until brown; add eggplant, bell pepper and zucchini.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from pot; set aside.
Bone chicken, cut into pieces.
Add to pot, cook until browned.
Stir in flour. Gradually add water and tomatoes with liquid from the can.
Add potatoes and seasonings, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add eggplant, zucchini and bell pepper, cook 5 more minutes.
Mix well, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill unopened can of milk until icy cold, about 3 to 4 hours. Dissolve gelatin in hot water; chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into gelatin mixture.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pour over gelatin mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm; cut in squares.

title: tender turkey and gravy(bake the day before)
directions: Remove giblets, tail, wing tips and some neck skin for dressing.
Wash in and out several times.
Drain.
Line roaster pan with foil, long enough to seal turkey in airtight (two 3 1/2-foot sheets, sealed together lengthwise with small folds).
Rub inside turkey with 3 tablespoons salt and outside with melted butter. Seal foil over turkey.
Bake in 325° oven 15 minutes per pound (5 hours).
Fold foil back last 30 minutes of baking time, to brown. Cool, drain and refrigerate bird and broth.
Next day, skim broth and heat.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and saute onion until soft and transparent.
Add chicken, tomato sauce, diced tomato, salsa, garlic powder and parsley; stir until blended well.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Place four corn tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour one-third of the chicken mixture over the top, spreading evenly layer one third of the cheese and one third of the olives on top of the chicken mixture.
Repeat layers two more times, ending with olives on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese is light brown and bubbly.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift flour.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve the rest for decorating.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate with M&M's on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tomato and sardine salad
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into slices. Chill. Drain oil from sardines. Remove skin and backbone. Arrange lettuce on a salad plate. Place tomato on it; cover with sardine, onion and lemon juice. Garnish with egg yolk which has been pressed through a sieve. Serves 6.

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl, combine first seven ingredients until creamy. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 25 appetizers.

title: tar heel pie
directions: Melt oleo; add chocolate chips and stir over low heat until they are melted.
Combine all other ingredients in another bowl. Pour the chocolate/oleo mixture into the other mixture and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Grate zucchini in hash brown form; mix in egg, flour and garlic.
Put 2 tablespoons of oil in frying pan and cook until done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Microwave broth, potato, carrot, celery, salt and pepper for 5 minutes.
Potato should be very soft.
Add corn.
Microwave again. Dump all in top of double boiler and add Cheddar cheese and milk. Stir thoroughly.
Heat until cheese melts, but do not boil.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Refrigerate in wax paper for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter/margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture and beat well.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumb 1/2 bag Doritos in bowl.
Brown 1/2 pound hamburg and drain.
Mix dry taco seasoning with hamburg.
Fix lettuce salad. Toss salad with hamburg mixture, Doritos and dressing.
I always double the recipe.

title: shortcake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to a stiff dough.
Work until smooth and pliable.
Leave for at least 1 hour in the refrigerator to get cold and firm.
Roll out thinly and cut into various shapes.
Bake in oven top rack until lightly browned.
Decorate with sugar, various frostings or sandwich together with jam.

title: elephant stew
directions: After about 60 days required to cut up elephant in cubes, place in 5-ton dish.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook at 325° about 4 weeks.
Cook Creamettes as directed; drain.
Do not chill. Mix immediately with elephant.
Serve hot.
Makes 3,752 servings.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients; mix well. Using pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine milk and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients, all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Don't overmix.
Spoon into cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: honey-mustard ham crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut each sheet of pastry into 6 triangles and place on flat, smooth surface.
In a small bowl, combine Worcestershire sauce, mustard and honey; stir well. Spread each triangle lightly with mustard mixture to within 1/4 inch of edges.
Place ham at the base of each triangle; roll up from base to point.
Ham will show at both sides.
Place, point side down, on ungreased baking sheet and twist slightly to curve. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and golden.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter. Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas.
Place on crust.
Layer as follows: pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts.
Garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa, soda and cold water well; set aside.
Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and flour. Mix well.
Add in the cocoa mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine meat, beef flavor mix, onions, eggs, catsup, bread crumbs and water.
Put into loaf pan.
Before baking, cover top with thin layer prepared mustard and top with croutons, then proceed with baking.
Bake about 60 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar, sugar, butter and pudding together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients.
Add butterscotch chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: lasagna pizza
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning mix (reserve 1 tablespoon for crust); simmer while preparing crust.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt margarine; mix
in
eggs
and cake mix.
Spread paste in	a
greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 2 eggs
and cream
cheese until smooth.
Spread on top of other mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in an oblong baking dish and freeze overnight.
Take out 30 to 60 minutes before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Clean and salt hen.
Boil gently until tender, then cool.
Pull meat from bones.
Cut white meat in larger chunks than dark meat. Add 1 cup chopped celery to every 2 cups chicken.
Add juice of 1 lemon and enough mayonnaise to make a moist salad.
Salt to taste and add cayenne pepper, if desired.

title: pineapple cake topping
directions: Mix all ingredients, leaving out the butter. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and stir to mix.
Spread on cooled cake.
Makes enough for two layers between and on top or on top of one long cake.

title: artichokes
directions: Wash artichokes.
Cut off approximately one inch of top of each artichoke, cutting straight across.
Cut off stem, leaving about 1/4 to 1/2 inch.
Pull off any loose leaves around bottom and clip off thorny tip of each leaf.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix everything together.
Put in ready-made pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes about 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: pork loin roast with braised red cabbage
directions: Place roast on rack in an open roasting pan.
Insert roast meat thermometer so that bulb is centered in thickest part.
Do not add water.
Do not cover.
Roast in a slow oven (325°) until the thermometer registers 170°.
Allow 30 to 35 minutes per pound.
Let roast stand in a warm place 15 to 20 minutes after removal from oven.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add onions and garlic and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cabbage, salt, fennel and white wine, stirring to combine.
Cover tightly and cook 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp.
Serve cabbage with carved pork roast.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Melt butter; cook onion lightly.
Brown.
Add other ingredients and cook 20 minutes.
Brown hamburger patties; add to mixture.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes until patties are done.
Good dish to keep warm in crock-pot; easily doubled.

title: cheddar chicken bake
directions: Prepare rice following package directions, adding the minced onion to the boiling water.
Fluff cooked rice and spread in greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with peas; arrange chicken over rice and peas.
Blend milk into soup and pour evenly over the chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs combined with melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barb and blair's tiny pea and corn salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill several hours, or better if a day or two.
Serve as a relish or on a bit of lettuce.

title: mosaic christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add 4x sugar.
Blend in egg, vanilla and flour. Stir in pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours in bowl. Divide into four, log-shaped pieces.
Roll in wax paper. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine cheese, tomato	sauce, garlic, chili powder and cumin and set aside.
In	large
bowl,
combine
lettuce	and chopped tomatoes.
Add Fritos,
ground
beef, onions and green pepper. Pour cheese sauce
over lettuce and meat mixture just before serving and toss.

title: brown sugar buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream both sugars and butter.
Add flour and eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake for approximately 35 minutes or until set.
Don't overbake as this will make the pie watery.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and saute onions and peppers until tender.
Add soups and broth and
jalapeno	pepper,
if desired. Add chopped chicken.
In a 9 x
13-inch
pan, spread 1/2 bag Doritos.
Spread half chicken and soup
mixture on top of chips. Top with 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat
layers.	Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip on a large serving platter.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream, taco mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: sheepherder's bread
directions: Dissolve sugar, yeast
and
salt
in warm water and let stand in	a warm place for 15 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl pour in liquid
ingredients.
Add oil and 4 cups flour.
Beat by hand 100 strokes.
If dough is not beaten sufficiently, the bread will
be heavy.
Add and stir well 3 1/2 to 4 cups flour or enough to make a stiff dough.
Sprinkle approximately 1 cup flour over
a bread board and turn dough onto it.
Knead until dough is
smooth
and elastic.
Use more flour if necessary to prevent
sticking.
This process
will take 10 to 15 minutes. Cover and
let rise 1 hour. Punch to original size.
Place in a
10-inch
Dutch
oven that is greased with butter, including the lid.
Cover and let dough rise until it touches the top of the lid.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, then add other ingredients and beat with egg beater until smooth, about 1 minute.
Bake in 8-inch greased square pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Mix spices.
Cut meat into 1/2-inch cube strips.
Mix meat and spices.
Stir until meat is well coated.
Marinate overnight. Place on rack over a drip pan.
Bake at 150° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: fajitas(club member: brad smith)
directions: Cut steak into small strips and let marinate at least 2 hours. Stir-fry onions and peppers; take out of pan.
Add meat and stir-fry until done; drain and put back into pan.
Add onions, peppers and tomato; cook for 1 minute.

title: yogurt coffee cake
directions: Stir together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, nuts and raisins.
Add yogurt, oil and eggs.
Stir until batter is smooth. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Stir together 2 tablespoons sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and coconut. Sprinkle mixture evenly on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In hot oil in Dutch oven, saute chicken.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Brown lightly.
Add tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, wine and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes. Serve on spaghetti.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Mix with the boiling water, then add oil.
(Add the food coloring with the water.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Clean carrots and slice.
Cook until tender.
Drain and add onions and peppers.
Mix soup, vinegar, oil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix until well blended in a food processor. Roll into two logs. Roll each log in paprika, then roll in chopped pecans.

title: home canned apple pie filling
directions: In a large saucepan, blend together sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in 10 cups water.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Pack apples (really cram them in as they cook down) into hot jars.
Fill with hot syrup; seal. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 quarts.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook, brown and drain sausage and onion.
Mix in sauerkraut, 2 tablespoons bread crumbs, cream cheese, mustard, salt and pepper. Refrigerate until cool.
Shape into balls.
Coat balls in the flour. Mix together eggs, and milk.
Dip floured balls into mixture.
Then roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Have ready: On separate pieces of wax paper, measure out salt and baking powder. Use a clean measuring spoon for each. Butter an extra-large piece of heavy-duty foil, about 30-inches long. (Can re-use for other batches.) Since I pull my brittle, I use 2 pairs of cotton gloves inside a pair of buttered plastic gloves.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Pat first 3 ingredient in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool thoroughly; mix cream cheese and sugar well; add Cool Whip, spread on crust.
Mix next 3 ingredients, put into refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups strawberries.
Spread on top of the cream cheese mixture and put in refrigerator.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Bring to a boil and stir until thick the sugar, water and cornstarch.
Separate the eggs.
Beat yolks; add to first mixture. Add lemon juice and rind and butter to mixture.
Put into cool, baked pie shell.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add bell pepper, onion, seasoned salt, 1 cup chopped nuts and pineapple; stir well. Shape into a ball and roll onto remaining one cup of chopped nuts. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple-pecan pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and stir well.
Add, vanilla, sugar, flour, eggs and nuts. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325 degrees.
Do not refrigerate.

title: hamburg vegetable chowder
directions: Brown beef in fat in large pot.
Put all ingredients (except potatoes and frozen vegetables) in with the browned beef.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook 30 minutes or longer. Add frozen vegetables and cook another 20 minutes.
Add salt if needed and perhaps more water to taste.
Better the day after it is made.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and shake in a jar.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: five grain cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add milk, vanilla, and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Gradually add cereal, stirring until well combined.
Drop by level tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: deviled egg surprise
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Add ham, carrots, salad dressing and mustard; stir well.
Fill egg halves with mixture.
Chill and sprinkle with paprika or garnish with fresh parsley.

title: sugarless jelly
directions: Cook fruit until done.
Add Jell-O and water, if needed.
Let cool to room temperature.
Put into refrigerator.
"Good made out of strawberries or Concord grapes."

title: easy mexican lasagna
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat 10 minutes or until heated. Stir together chicken and mushroom soups and enchilada sauce in a saucepan; cook, stirring often, 10 minutes. Spoon 1/3 of sauce into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray topped with 3 tortillas. Spoon half of chicken mixture and 1/3 sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with half Cheddar cheese. Top with 3 tortillas; spoon half of chicken mixture and 1/3 sauce over tortillas. Sprinkle with half of Cheddar cheese. Top with 3 tortillas. Repeat layers once with sauce, Cheddar cheese and tortillas, ending with Monterey Jack cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes, until bubbly. Serve with toppings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of the pudding over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Add remaining pudding, then another layer of graham crackers close together.
Ice with milk chocolate icing.
Make 1 day in advance.
Refrigerate.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and	butter until fluffy.
Add sugar slowly, beating after each	addition.
Add	one egg at a time, beating after each egg.
Add
milk	and beat well.	Add 2 cups flour; mix well then add 1 cup of flour.
Beat well.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add
flavor
and
mix again.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggless fruit cake
directions: Boil together 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add 4 cups flour.
Bake in 4 layers.
Put together with desired frosting.

title: rob's fried fish
directions: Saturday, wake up at 4:00 a.m. and drive 6 hours.
Fish all day, "no fish", go to motel.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut
spareribs into portions and place in the bottom of a roasting pan.
Season to taste.
Add sauerkraut.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Make dumplings by combining the flour, baking powder, milk and egg.
Drop by spoonfuls on the sauerkraut. Cover
pan
tightly
and
finish
baking
for
30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients with 1/2 can V-8 juice.
Bake.
Pour 1/2 can V-8 juice over top of meat loaf.

title: flautas
directions: Mix together refried beans, Monterey Jack cheese, cumin and garlic powder.
Put in double boiler or microwave oven until spreading consistency.

title: easy rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening; let stand until lukewarm. Dissolve yeast cakes in small amount of water.
Add to shortening and boiling water and gradually add the other ingredients.

title: red, white and blue layer dessert
directions: Bottom Layer:
Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Cool.
Add pineapple.
Pour into bottom of mold.
Chill until firm but slightly sticky to touch.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: If stiff, add milk.
If juicy, add confectioners sugar.
Can add a few nuts in icing, if preferred.

title: carrot bread
directions: Pour batter into one large or two small bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (less for small pans).

title: meringue torte
directions: Beat until foamy the egg whites and add
a pinch of salt, cream of tartar and sugar, gradually.
Continue beating 10 minutes.
Pour into well-greased rectangular 9 x 14-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Cool.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add
biscuit
mix	and vanilla; mix well.	Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Press chocolate kiss in center of each ball immediately after baking.

title: easy summer salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Mix together.

title: potato surprise
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on box.
Before baking, add the remaining ingredients and stir well.
May have to add a little more milk.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: crab and artichoke dip
directions: Mix everything together.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with crackers or pita toast points.

title: honey jelly
directions: Combine honey, apple juice and lemon juice in a large pan. Bring quickly to a rolling boil and stir in pectin.
Bring back to a full boil that cannot be stirred down.
Remove from heat and skim foam that appears on top.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal with paraffin.
Store in a cool dry place.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: potato dressing
directions: Boil until thick, then mix salad dressing, about 50-50 with it. I use Miracle Whip.
Use on potato salad.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Mix the soups in a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir in the beef; cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours or until tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers (sliced), green peppers, ice and onions in layers in a crock with salt.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight or 6 hours.
Drain.
Make a syrup of vinegar, sugar and spices.
Add these to cucumbers.
Heat slowly with very little stirring.
Scald, do not boil.
Place pickles in sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: sweet potato pie casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 15 minutes in casserole dish.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese over a completely cooled crust.
Top with one layer of fresh whole berries.
Mix remainder of berries mashed with enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add sugar and cornstarch. Allow to thicken over low heat; cool and pour over cheese.
Top with whipped cream.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix all and put in buttered dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix 2 tablespoons butter, melted with 1 cup cornflake crumbs and top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best when mixed ahead of time and left in refrigerator overnight.

title: gramma' applesauce stacked cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in cast iron frying pan, greased lightly.
Cover with lid.
Make 1 1/2-inch cakes; turn when brown. Turn out on plate to cool.
Makes about 10 to 12.

title: grandma's swedish meatballs
directions: Mix onion, bell pepper and a little water in blender and set aside.
Mix sausage, beef, egg, bread and seasoning.
Add onion and pepper mixture.
Place in the refrigerator in a gallon bag overnight.
Roll mixture into balls.
Brown in a skillet on medium heat.
Place in crock-pot with sauce.
Cook on high for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: `Mix all together except cabbage and tomatoes.
Put head of cabbage in boiling water until leaves separate.
Put about 1 tablespoon meat mixture in each leaf; roll up well.
Add water about halfway over rolls and cook about 1 hour.
Add tomatoes or tomato soup when almost done.

title: texas mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Brown the beef; add celery, green pepper and onion together.
Cook until tender.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Add dinner.
Mix well.

title: onion sage dressing
directions: Heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add onions, celery and sage.
Cook, stirring, until onions are golden, approximately 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Toss, transfer to 1-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings; each serving contains 90 calories.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions, adding the additional milk.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Remove from heat and add cream.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: fish chowder
directions: Melt half of the margarine in a large, heavy kettle over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, thyme, parsley, pepper and oregano. Saute until onion is translucent.
Add vermouth.
Drain the liquid from clams and set aside with rinsed shrimp.
Stir in fish chunks; cover and simmer until fish is firm and opaque (about 10 minutes) over medium heat.
Stir in soup, milk, shrimp and clams.
Heat, stirring often, until steaming.
Pour into tureen and add rest of the margarine.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: *corned beef barbecue
directions: Cook until thick, about 4 hours.
May be served on bun with cole slaw.
Serves 4.

title: lime and cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water. Let cool. Whip in mixer briefly.
Add whipping cream and beat until thickened.
Stir in cottage cheese until well mixed.
Pour into mold and set in refrigerator.
Dissolve lime jello in hot water.
Let cool.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts: stir well.
Pour on top of lemon and cottage cheese mixture in mold: return to refrigerator to set.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Fold in German chocolate and chocolate chips.

title: salmon canapes
directions: Flake salmon and combine with cheese, mayonnaise, green onion, parsley and garlic powder.
Separate rolls in thin rounds and place on cookie sheet.
Top with salmon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Spread batter in a greased pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon together and sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.
Good with whipped topping.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic and onion until soft.
Add meat and salt; brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or more.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: In large punch bowl, cranberry juice.
Real lemon and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add orange soda, liqueurs if desired and ice.
Garnish as desired.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: artichokes and green beans romano
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until transparent.
Stir in bread crumbs, blending well to absorb oil. Add beans, artichokes and cheese.
Combine thoroughly, yet gently. Heat slowly to soften cheese.
Season to taste with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Serves 4.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook 1 hour at 300° or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds. Place in baking dish and sprinkle with almonds. Heat at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve with Triscuits and crostini.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick, approximately 7 minutes.
Serve over cooked and drained vegetables.

title: fruit or vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Good with fruit or vegetables.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients
except the coconut.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour
into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Let
stand
minutes,
then sprinkle coconut on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour two 9-inch cake pans. Combine all the ingredients for the layers in a large mixing bowl.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes. Batter should be thick but smooth.
Divide the batter evenly between the prepared pans. Bake for about 20 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center of the layers. Cool completely on racks.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Gradually add orange juice to achieve desired dough consistency.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll each ball in coconut.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, cocoa, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Over medium heat, slowly stir in water; heat through, stirring occasionally.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream
together
margarine, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, salt, soda
and
cinnamon;
mix well with first mixture.	Add sliced, cored
and	peeled	apples;
mix
well.
Spoon
into ungreased baking
pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until well browned.

title: nina's bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, yeast, baking soda and baking powder together in mixer bowl.
Warm milk (don't boil), then cool to lukewarm.
Mix and pour in mixer bowl with flour mixture.
Mix well; put in large, greased bowl.
Also, grease the top.
Put in refrigerator.
Will keep a week or longer.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine all together. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Remove and place in small containers.
Store in freezer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onion and margarine.
Add garlic, paprika, flour, salt and black pepper.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until very brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Add mushrooms, soup and sour cream. Cook on low about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole, make a layer of half the ingredients.
Season with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Make another layer, top with bread crumbs or Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: For 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave at High for 1 minute.
Peanuts will be lightly brown and syrup will be very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Then break into small pieces.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix together as given and bake at 350°.

title: grilled chicken breast on sourdough
directions: Spray grill or broiling pan with nonstick cooking spray. Grill or broil chicken 5 inches from heat 8 minutes, turning over halfway.
Cut pepper into rings.
Thinly slice basil on top.
Put 4 slices of bread with all the ingredients and cover with bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Brown chops on both sides in shortening.
Pour off excess fat.
Pour sauce over chops.
Cover; simmer about 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: anna's super duper bars
directions: Cook dates, hot water and 1 teaspoon of soda until mushy. Then cool.
Add margarine, white sugar and eggs.
Mix well and add flour, cocoa and salt.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread on top the chocolate bits and walnuts, cut up.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: zesty fries
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Pour in frozen French fries; cook until golden brown.
Drain.
Sprinkle on garlic powder and seasoned salt to your own taste.

title: favorite company breakfast
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cubed bread and ham in pan, cover with cheese and soup.
Season.
Beat eggs until frothy, add milk.
Pour over bread, meat, cheese, etc. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook on high 3 hours with lid on and 4 hours with lid off. This will require occasional stirring.

title: swiss cheese fondue
directions: Add cornstarch, nutmeg, pepper and salt to cheese. Toss lightly with fork to combine. Add wine to 3-quart saucepan (or earthenware to keep heat longer). Cook over low heat until it begins to bubble gently.
Add cheese, a handful at a time, stirring rigorously with a wooden spoon until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly blended. Serve immediately with bread cubes.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: Make stock using whole chicken parts.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Strain liquid and put back in pot.
In food processor, process reserved onions, carrots and celery separately.
Bring liquid to a boil and add vegetables plus 3 to 4 tablespoons of small pasta (orzo).
Continue cooking about 15 minutes.
Make a roux with 3 to 4 tablespoons flour and 3 to 4 tablespoons margarine.
Add to the simmering soup.
Add chicken and serve.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Milk chocolate is a double boiler.
Remove from fire.
Add butter, then condensed milk and vanilla, stirring well.
As soon as mixture begins to thicken, drop from spoon onto a buttered baking sheet.
Add toasted nuts or raisins or roll in chopped nuts.

title: jello dream
directions: Mix cheese and jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and mix. Mix by hand only.

title: scallop fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. If mixture is too thick, you will need to add a little more water. Mixture should be like a thick pancake. Drop 1/4 cup mixture for each fritter. Fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Heat oil in saucepot. Add beef and cook until browned. Pour off fat. Add mushroom soup, 1 cup water and soup mix. Heat to a boil. Cover over low heat 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and carrots. Cover and cook 1 hour or until roast is fork-tender. Remove roast and vegetables to platter.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Put all into one bowl.
Mix all together.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Grease 2
loaf pans lightly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: one dish mexican dinner
directions: Place 6 tortillas in bottom of long cake pan (13 x 9-inch). Brown meat.
Add chili powder.
Drain.
Spread meat over tortillas. Spread beans over meat.
Slice cheese thin and spread over beans. Cover with 6 tortillas.

title: taffy
directions: Boil syrup, sugar and vinegar 10 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool enough to pull.

title: italian chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Cook and stir garlic in oil in large skillet over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add chicken; stir-fry until no longer pink.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm.
Add zucchini; stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Return chicken to skillet with tomato halves and dressing.
Heat through.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Brown ground chuck, sausage, onion, garlic and bell pepper. Pour off grease. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce, cumin, oregano, Accent, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes. Add rice to meat mixture. Put in braised pepper cups. Top with Parmesan cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: casserole for a crowd(hamburger-noodle bake)
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper, half at a time, until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook noodles according to package; drain well.
Return noodles to kettle.
Stir in meat mixture, tomato soup, cheese, chili sauce, pimento, salt, chili powder, pepper and 2 cups water.
Mix well.
Divide mixture between 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) baking dishes.

title: sara's quick rolls
directions: Put dry ingredients into bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix together oil, buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients, mixing well.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Make into favorite rolls.
I roll out and cut as for biscuits.
Dip into melted margarine and fold over.
Let rise in pan 10 or 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Heat electric broiler (not necessary to heat gas broiler). Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Cut shells in half crosswise.
Fry in deep hot oil, 375°, for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown; drain.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with process cheese spread; broil until process cheese spread begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix in tomato soup, cream of chicken soup and corn.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can also add cooked macaroni if desired.

title: microwave s'more bars
directions: Place corn syrup and butter in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate is melted.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream
sugar,
shortening and margarine.
Add
cocoa and eggs, one at a time, salt, vanilla, coloring, baking powder, flour and milk.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: barbecue for sandwiches
directions: Brown the ground beef with salt, pepper and onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat through and serve.

title: lois mays' mini biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits, in a small pan and melt.
Dip and roll biscuits in mixture until thoroughly covered. Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add milk; stir. Add Bisquick (dry) and stir.
Add cheese.
Stir in browned sausage.
Pour into buttered 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and solid.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, milk, salt and orange rind.
Scoop 1/4 cup mixture and shape around each marshmallow. Use more potatoes if needed.
Roll each ball in cornflakes.
Place on buttered baking dish.
Cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to use, bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: forgotten chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and add 3 cans soup.
Stir in hot water.
Add rice.
Mix all well in dish.
Salt and pepper chicken and lay on top.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or until done.

title: gingerbread deluxe
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Sift the flour, salt, soda and ginger. Stir ingredients together until smooth. Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pan. Bake at 325°. Serve hot with applesauce, whip cream or chocolate sauce.

title: chicken wing pacifica
directions: Disjoint chicken wing and discard boney tips.
Arrange meatier wing parts in shallow baking pan.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, garlic powder and sour cream together in medium bowl.
Coarsely flake tuna in a large bowl.
Add peas, celery, water chestnuts and pineapple.
Toss lightly with dressing.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Cook artichokes; remove core and stuff with tuna salad.
Right before serving, toss chow mein noodles into salad.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: ultra delicious apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in shortening.
Add milk.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut in 4 squares.
Place apple on each square and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Fold and pinch edges together.
Place in baking dish and put Syrup (recipe follows) over all.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Baste 3 or 4 times during baking time with Syrup.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pat the mixture into
a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt the chocolate morsels in a separate container and pour over first mixture. Chill 30 minutes and cut into squares.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Blend avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Blend bean dip until smooth. Spread in a 9x13 dish in the following order:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, shallots, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: orange jello carrot salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple with ReaLemon and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add orange Jell-O to pineapple mixture and mix well.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Cool Jell-O mixture, then add cheese and grated carrots to pineapple and Jell-O mixture. Mix Cool Whip (thawed) into Jell-O mixture.
Save some cheese and chopped nuts for top when ready to serve.

title: quick meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix
together
and
store
in a jar or can with a tight lid. Use about 1/4 cup mix; fill cup with hot water.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake covered for 15 minutes in preheated oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened. Pour heated sauce over chicken, then top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: company chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken breast with 2 pieces of dried beef and then wrap with 1 piece of bacon to make a roll.
Place slice of cream cheese on top of each roll and surround with cream of chicken soup in a casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Using mixer, cream sugars, butter and oil; add vanilla and eggs. Gradually mix in dry ingredients.
Mix in pecans.
Roll by teaspoons into sugar, place on cookie sheet and mash with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove when cookies are light brown.
They become crispy when cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen. Really good.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown together ground beef and sausage; drain.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle meat/sausage mixture over the top.
Mix together the soup, cheese, salt, pepper and 1 can water; pour over potato-meat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with extra cheese, if you desire, while still hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken stewed with bell peppers
directions: Wash and dry chicken, cut into medium size serving pieces and flour them lightly.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Brown chicken pieces over moderate heat for 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper when done and pour wine over.
Cook until wine evaporates almost completely.
Continue cooking until well done, moistening the meat from time to time with a bit of the stock.

title: indian corn
directions: Fry bacon in a 9-inch skillet until crisp; remove bacon and add all the mentioned ingredients.
Cover and cook approximately 9 minutes.
Remove from skillet and crumble crisp bacon on top. Serves 4.

title: freckles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch square pan and set aside.

title: mary ellen's lasagne
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water, basil, garlic and 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased casserole. Place in pan of water in a 350° oven.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Top with grated cheese last 10 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk, then cool.
Add sugar, salt, oil, eggs and yeast. Last, add flour.
Mix well.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Work bread dough well with hands; divide into 24 pieces.
With Crisco on hands, shape into individual pieces.
Place onto well-greased pan.
Cover.
Let dough rise to double in size.
Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, bacon, green onions and raisins together.

title: sour cream noodle-bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Saute beef in butter.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce to meat.
Simmer over low heat 5 minutes.

title: bubble bread #1
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
After bread unthaws, roll into small balls.
Roll balls in melted margarine, then roll to cover in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Let rise up in a tube pan. If you have margarine and cinnamon mixture left, pour over all. You may add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then invert onto a plate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Thinly shred both cabbages, discarding cores.
Place in a large bowl.
Chop apples leaving skins on and add to cabbage.
Add chopped nuts.

title: wing's famous popcorn balls
directions: In a large pot or bowl, butter bottom and sides.
Pour in popped popcorn.
Over medium heat cook sugar, water, molasses, butter, salt and vanilla.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally. To test if it is done, pour some cold water in a small bowl; pour a tablespoon of molasses mixture.
If you can pick it up in a ball, it's ready to be poured over popcorn.
Mix well.
Cool slightly and form into balls.

title: thomasson pork chops
directions: In skillet (with little oil or sprayed with cooking oil), brown chops on both sides (about 10 minutes).
Add soup, about 1 can of water, carrots, potatoes, mushrooms and onion.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Can use any other choice of vegetables.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Add the shortening and mix well (like a pie crust).
Add the buttermilk.
Roll the dough 3/4 inch thick.
Make circles with a cutter or glass.
Cook at 375° until lightly brown.

title: christian home
directions: Put water in pot (somewhat similar to a cup in shape, but larger, usually made of some sort of metal and often has a long handle). Pot should be large enough to hold all the water you want to boil. If it isn't you can divide your water in half, but the first half gets cold while you boil the second half. Light burner under pot. Cook until bubbles appear. Keep eyes closed during later part of this process as a watched pot never boils.

title: cheese scalloped corn
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add corn, milk, cracker crumbs, onion, green pepper, cheese, salt and pepper. Spoon into a 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place points to center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan. Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Crust will be puffy.
Spoon cooked sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine eggs, milk, oregano and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate and sugar dissolves.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; stir until lukewarm, then add vanilla.
Beat until thick and no longer glossy.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut when set.

title: calico corn muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and red pepper.
Stir in milk, egg and margarine just until blended (batter will be slightly lumpy).
Stir in corn, chopped red pepper and onions until just mixed.
Spoon mixture into 12 lightly greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
Serve warm at room temperature.

title: company cake
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice when baking cake mix.
Bake cake mix in a jelly roll tray.
Cool.
Beat together cheese, milk and pudding.
Add crushed pineapple.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread on the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Dot with walnuts and chill.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese thinly on pizza pan.
Top with sauce.
Top with green onions, black olives, and shredded taco cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in blender at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Chop the apricots very fine or grind them.
Mix with coconut and milk.
Make small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: plantation brownies(with caramel icing)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, cocoa, flour, pecans and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan . Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix first five ingredients until uniform.
Spoon into a well greased casserole dish.
Pour milk over mixture.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat the egg, milk and margarine.
Add egg mixture and sour cream to flour mixture.
Stir until just blended.
Pour mixture into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden and wooden toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Yield:
about 9 servings.

title: antha's cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes and place all ingredients into microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Do not cover or cheese will burn at the edges.
If it is too liquid, add more cheese.
If too thick, add milk or salsa, whichever you desire.
(Monterey Jack can be substituted for Cheddar.)

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with crackers.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread 1/2 pudding mix on crackers. Place second layer crackers.
Add another layer of pudding.
Add final layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain and add spaghetti mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer gently.
Spread meat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese and sour cream.
Top with crescent rolls; brush with butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, oleo and nuts.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: country corn casserole
directions: Combine cheese and eggs until blended. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in 3 quarts of boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into well-buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Shake chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Brown and put in glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple, pouring syrup into 2-cup measure.
Add water to make 1 1/4 cups.
In saucepan, combine sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon.
When mixture begins to boil, take out 1/2 cup and mix with cornstarch.
Stir until smooth.
Add to rest of sauce and stir constantly while it boils for 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Add pineapple slices and green pepper.
Bake 30 minutes longer until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate, milk and butter.
Combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold into mixture. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Slice and remove from pan. Keep refrigerated.

title: crawfish etouffee
