directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter until tender. Stir in flour and then tomato sauce.
Let simmer for 10 minutes. Add seasoned crawfish and cook on medium fire for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
(Batter will be stiff.) Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pig-out cake
directions: Liquefy Mandarin oranges in blender (including juice).
Mix cake mix, oil, oranges and eggs.
Pour into 3 round, greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Place the egg yolks in the top of double boiler.
Add sugar and salt.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Add cider vinegar and cornstarch that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Cook over boiling water until thick and smooth, about 12 minutes.

title: onion-mushroom rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add rice and lightly brown.
Add onion soup mix and stir.
Add water and stir.
Add drained mushrooms.
Simmer until water is absorbed in rice.
This is a good side dish for chicken.

title: buffalo style chicken wings
directions: Cut tips of chicken wings.
Halve remaining chicken wings at joint.
In food processor or blender, process soup mix, butter, vinegar, water, garlic, pepper and cumin until blended; set aside.

title: he-man loaf
directions: Reserve 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in only enough of the reserved flour to make soft dough on floured surface.
Knead for four minutes.
On greased baking sheet, roll or pat dough to fit cookie sheet.
Spread dressing down center, top with slices of onion, bell pepper; layer ham, roast beef and cheese.
Cut 1 inch wide strips along sides of filling out to edge of dough.
Crisscross strips over top of filling.
Cover dough; place sheet in warm place for 15 minutes.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown on top. Slice and serve while warm.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 400 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: muskrat
directions: Rinse muskrat pieces several times until rinse water is clear; drain well. Dredge muskrat pieces with flour. Fry in oil in skillet until lightly browned; season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove to roasting pan.
Arrange onions and bacon in roaster. Sprinkle with sage. Add water. Roast, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add berries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture in Pyrex dish and congeal.
Add sour cream over this. Then pour rest of mixture over this and congeal.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits well.
Mix fruits.
Place in casserole.
Spread applesauce on top of fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon candy.
Bake at 350° for 30 or more minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat butter until
fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat after each cup until fluffy.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture is like whipped cream.
Mix dry ingredients to butter mixture, adding flour alternating with milk.
Pour into 4 (9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Arrange fruit in a glass lasagne dish. Sprinkle with the brown sugar, salt, lemon juice and curry. Add the fruit juice and spot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: nestle chocolate angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven according to cake mix directions.
Combine cocoa and cake mix (or flour).
Prepare, bake and cool angel food cake according to cake mix directions.
Sift confectioners sugar over top of cake.
Serve with strawberries.
Yields 12 servings. Contains 157 calories, 0 mg cholesterol, 0.6 g fat and 142 mg sodium.

title: butter frosting
directions: In a bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Blend in egg yolk.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Yields 2 cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix stuffing according to box. Brown sausage.
Saute onions and mushroom stems in some of the sausage drippings.
Combine together.
Fill mushroom caps; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: grandma mag's oatmeal cake
directions: Mix hot water and oatmeal.
Set aside.
Mix butter, sugars and eggs.
Add oatmeal, then dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: garlic pepper steak
directions: Add all ingredients in medium container.
Marinate meat overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Drain.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.

title: date fingers
directions: Blend sugar, butter, egg and dates over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Let stand long enough to cool.
Cut and roll in nuts or coconut.

title: halibut casserole with asparagus
directions: Place fish in boiling milk with the bay leaf.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 8 minutes or until fish turns opaque and will flake. Lift fish out and drain.
Remove bay leaf and reserve milk.
Remove skin and bones and break fish into small chunks.
Put fish into a buttered casserole.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and stir in the flour, pepper and paprika.
Add the reserved hot milk and stir with a whisk.
Add grated onion and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over fish in casserole.
Arrange the asparagus spears on top.
Sprinkle with the combined bread crumbs, cheese, melted butter and lemon juice.
Bake for 10 minutes or until heated through and bubbling.
Serves 6.

title: graham cracker dream bars
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt 1 cup butter; add milk, sugar and egg.
Cook in double boiler until slightly thickened.
Add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Cool slightly.
Pour over whole graham crackers in pan, then cover with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Mix together powdered sugar, 1/2 cup butter and vanilla or lemon extract.
Thin with milk to spreading consistency.
Spread over graham crackers, chill and cut in squares.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: In food processor or blender, crush cookies until fine; set aside.
In bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and sugar until smooth. In another bowl, mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
In flowerpot, alternate layers of cookie mixture and pudding mixture, ending with cookies.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Decorate with silk flower and worms.
Yields 12 servings.

title: wholesome holiday snacks
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels,
peanuts, sunflower seeds and wheat germ.
In a small
saucepan,
combine honey, brown sugar and butter; stir over low heat	until mixture is smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture, tossing to	coat
evenly.
Spread
in
a large and shallow pan.
Bake at
275° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. (Cereal may seem soft,
but
crisps
upon cooling).
Cool, stirring occasionally;
break
up
to
separate. Store in medium canister.

title: homemade pancake syrup
directions: Mix together sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add remaining ingredients.
Let boil until syrupy.

title: cheezy buttons
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick and butter.
Stir in water and sesame seed until dough forms a ball.
Drop scant teaspoonful into cheese.
Shape into balls or ovals.
Place on ungreased baking sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake until golden brown in 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients plus a small amount of food coloring and mix for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° in small muffin pans for 10 minutes.
Combine last 4 ingredients plus a small amount of food coloring and mix.
Dip blossom in this icing or pour over them and place on waxed paper to dry.

title: caribbean barbecue
directions: Trim any fat from pork as needed.
Thinly slice red onion. Place pork and onions in a nonmetal baking dish.
Combine lime juice, salt and cayenne; pour over pork.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Just before removing from oven, top with grated cheese.
To freeze, do not cook prior to freezing. Serves 16.

title: party pumpkin pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry and cool in refrigerator. Melt butter.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Beat eggs until frothy. Mix flour, sugar, salt and milk.
Add to egg mixture.
Add to pumpkin mixture and stir gently.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 40 minutes longer.
Test with knife.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.

title: tangy brown pork chops
directions: Place meat in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake 45 minutes at 375°; drain fat off.
Combine onion, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Spread on meat.
Pour on tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and cook until thick.
Add jello and coloring.
Let cool.
Line a baked pastry shell with berries.
Pour mixture over berries.
Place in refrigerator and let congeal.
Top with whipped cream (optional) or Cool Whip.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Mix well and microwave for 10 minutes.

title: glazed frank hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each frank into 8 pieces.
Mix preserves with mustard and pour over franks.
Simmer over medium heat until heated thoroughly.
Serve from chafing dish or electric fondue pot.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients until smooth.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking about 35 minutes or until custard is firm.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
In the same mixing bowl, mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread this mixture over the cake batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: split seconds
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Blend in butter or margarine, egg and vanilla to form a soft dough.

title: buffington's flank roast
directions: Bake 1 hour per pound at 250°.
Roast may be any size but still use same amount of ingredients as listed.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 can of tomato sauce.
Divide into 2 large loaves.
Cover each with remaining can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and heat in microwave 2 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Spread on potatoes; bake 15 minutes.

title: johnny musette
directions: Cook onion and turkey in oil until brown; drain well.
Cook noodles as directed, but slightly under done.
Drain well.
Add corn, soup, sauce, meat and most of the cheese.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: escalloped corn and cheese
directions: Pour egg into a 6-cup buttered casserole.
Heat corn and milk. Gradually stir egg into the beater.
Add salt, bread crumbs and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake uncovered in a moderately slow 325° oven for 30 minutes or until custard tests done.
Yields 5 servings.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add enough flour to handle like biscuits.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Use 2 pieces of dough for each cookie.
Crimp edges together after filling and pierce tops with a fork.

title: robin's fresh corn casserole
directions: Thaw corn; chop in food processor.
Transfer to bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Line bottom of shallow casserole.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, olive oil and red pepper flakes in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until well coated.
Place on baking sheet, in single layer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn after 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with basil. Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time alternately with flour and buttermilk and beat well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix green chilies, taco mix and water.
Layer in a 9 x 13 casserole dish the beans, sour cream, meat (pat to remove oil and cool), picante sauce and cheese.
Add green chilie mixture to meat after oil is removed and cooled.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg; mix until smooth.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator. Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and crabmeat in large bowl.
Shape into a ball with a hole in the center.
Pour cocktail sauce in the center.
Serve with Ritz crackers and enjoy.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Combine nuts, coconut, gelatin, condensed milk and vanilla. Work until smoothly mixed.
Form into a ball and refrigerate an hour at least.
Shape a small ball of the chilled mixture into the shape of a strawberry.
Use about a tablespoonful.
Chill on a tray of waxed paper again after all berries are formed.
Roll in red sugar.
Use almonds tinted green for stems or purchase plastic stems from cake and party supply store.
Refrigerate in airtight container until serving time.
Makes about 45 strawberries.

title: rosamarina or frog eye salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Pour the juice from all the fruit into a large saucepan.
Mix all the fruit in a large mixing bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar with the fruit juices.
Add the cornstarch; mix until lumps are gone.
Turn on the heat and stir constantly with a wire whisk until mixture becomes consistency of pudding.
Be careful not to let it burn on the bottom.
Once done, set aside and stir occasionally until cooked.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Fry out your beef and bacon.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in crock-pot and simmer for approximately 6 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.	Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes, remove from pan and let cool completely.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for at least an hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown almonds in bacon drippings or small amount of margarine. Drain on paper towels.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside. In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture. Mix well. Stir in chips and nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: blueberry corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners. Sift cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour buttermilk, egg and butter into the well.
Stir until just combined.
Fold in blueberries until just combined.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape like strawberries.
They handle better if mixture stands awhile.
Roll in red sugar.
Use frosting for green leaves.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: Over medium-high heat in large saucepan, cook garlic in 1 tablespoon margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth, peas, carrots and seasonings. Set aside.

title: chili con queso cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients into crock pot and let simmer until cheese melts.

title: 15 minute creamy fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini noodles as directed; drain.
All all ingredients and cook over low heat until smooth about 5 minutes.

title: one layer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Bake in one 9-inch round or square cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Great dessert for two.

title: devil ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Mix with drained corn.
Dice bell pepper and tomatoes and mix together.
Combine dressing, mayo and sour cream.
Prepare corn bread per package.
Let cool.
Layer: corn bread, pinto beans, pepper, tomato, cheese, corn-bacon mix, dressing combo and repeat.
Top with remaining corn bread, sprinkled on top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and salsa.
Put in 9-inch pie plate and layer with vegetables.
Top with Cheddar cheese and black olives.
To make it low-fat, use fat-free cream cheese and low-fat Cheddar.
Enjoy with tortilla chips.
Yummy!

title: creamy dreamy cheese cake
directions: Line 13x9 pan with crushed graham crackers.

title: crabmeat hot dish
directions: Put half bread in pan.
Saute celery, pepper and onion in butter.
Spread over bread.
Mix with fish and mayonnaise.
Beat eggs well; add milk and pour over.
Let stand overnight.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Spread soup and cheese mixed over top and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer and repeat the lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and frozen peas.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar.
Spread over salad. Garnish with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Mix before serving.

title: favorite chicken hot dish
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer noodles, chicken, soups, cheese, mushrooms and asparagus.
Top layer should be soup and cheese.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine all ingredients with small amount of the tomato sauce (1/2 of can).
Pile into halved peppers.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over each pepper.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour or more, if necessary.
If peppers are small, do not halve.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Combine hot dogs
(cut up), potatoes, onions and margarine. Combine peas,
mustard and mushroom soup.
Put with hot dog mixture.
Cover with foil.	Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: In a heavy sauce pan put butter, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and oatmeal; mix good.
Drop on cookie sheet.

title: excellent chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Mix together sauce ingredients and spread over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish. Blend cream cheese, chopped onion and milk until smooth.
Pour on top of spinach and mix lightly.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken packets(a quick meal from freezer to table.)
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, milk and salt (work with your hands to mix).
Store this in a 1-quart freezer bag.
Put crouton crumbs in another 1-quart freezer bag.
Tape to chicken bag.
Freeze. Refrigerate crescent rolls.

title: cheese and bacon ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with a spoon.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan at 325° until done.
Cool and frost.
The longer the cake sits the moistier it becomes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and meal.
Beat egg yolks with spoon and mix in warm water.
Add all together and cook stirring until thick. Add lemon juice and margarine; pour into a cool baked pie shell. Top with meringue and brown 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brat appetizer
directions: Brown brats.
Slice into bite size pieces.
Combine first 3 ingredients. Pour mixture over brats and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Cream the shortening in a large bowl.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Unthaw enough to work together.
(For the real pros, use your own dough.)
Roll out, butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut into 12 rolls.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, tomato, cheese, lettuce and dressing together in large mixing bowl.
Add chips shortly before serving to prevent soggy chips.
Mix crushed chips into concoction.
Try and eat all of the salad within a couple of days; it does not age well.
Serves 10 comfortably.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour off any fat.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil, then the pumpkin.
Mix well. Combine flour, spice, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Pour pumpkin mixture into the well.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cranberries.
Spoon batter into two 8 x 3 x 3-inch greased baking pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until tester comes out clean.
Very nice for Christmas gifts.

title: dustin's blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients, just until flour and sugar are moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Immediately remove from pan.

title: sausage pasta stew
directions: In 5-quart or 6-quart Dutch oven cook sausage, sweet pepper, onions and garlic over medium heat until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat and pat meat and vegetables with paper towels to remove excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, broth, sugar, basil, oregano and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Stir in pasta.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes more or until pasta is just tender.
Ladle into bowls.
Garnish with herbs if desired.

title: corn custard
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thick.
Add seasonings, corn, beaten egg and green pepper. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix until creamy the sugars, butter, oil and egg. Add vanilla; mix. Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt together. Add to the creamy mixture. Add coconut, nuts and Rice Krispies; mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoons. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: green beans supreme
directions: In frypan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove, drain and crumble. Save about 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Add soup, milk and beans.
Heat; stir often. Garnish with bacon.

title: grandpa william's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and simmer for 4 to 6 hours until meat and vegetables are done.
Serve over boiled spaghetti.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Form into a ball. Chill overnight.
Roll cheese ball in pecans and parsley.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine ground beef, 1/2 jar salsa, eggs and bread crumbs.
Season.
If adding cheese, do so now. Press into loaf pan.
Pour remaining salsa on top.
Bake to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef hot dish
directions: Mix noodles together with rest of ingredients. Break crumbs or potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie salad #2
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Add ground round and lightly brown. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Do not drain beans.)
Mix. Simmer in a covered baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; salt and pepper to taste.
Add spaghetti sauce after draining hamburger.
Cook noodles and drain.
Put half of noodles in bottom of a large dish.
Pour half of sauce mixture on noodles.
Spread cottage cheese over sauce mixture.
Add rest of noodles.
Place Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southwest stew
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions; drain. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes. Garnish with shredded cheese, if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: easter eggs
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it reaches 240° on candy thermometer.
Take out 1 cup of syrup from pan and add 2 beaten egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Continue cooking pan of syrup until it reaches 265°.
Pour slowly into mixture.
Beat until it forms a peak.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
You can add cherries, nuts and coconut to mixture or leave plain.
Butter hands and work mixture like dough; shape into eggs.
Cool in refrigerator.
Melt 1 large Hershey plain candy bar and coat eggs in chocolate.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Spread on pizza crust.
Add toppings as desired.
Makes enough sauce for 1 large pizza.
We mix onions, green pepper, olives and mushrooms into the sauce before spreading it on the pizza.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix together in large bowl, pour into very well greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not flour pie plate.

title: perfect oyster stew
directions: Combine the flour, salt, pepper and water.
Blend together to make a smooth paste.
Stir into the oysters with their liquid in saucepan over low heat.
Simmer oysters over low heat until edges curl.
Pour into the milk.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 10 or 15 minutes to improve flavor.
Add the butter or margarine and reheat briefly.
Rinse soup tureen and/or soup plates with hot water so soup will stay piping hot.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: sicilian cassata cake
directions: Use large mixing bowl. Sift 1/2 cup of sugar with flour several times to blend well. Place egg yolks, water and grated lemon rind in bowl. Beat lightly. Add almond extract. Gradually sift flour very lightly over beaten egg yolks. Fold in gently.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: savory potatoes
directions: Peel 6 potatoes and cut into quarters or thick slices.
Dry on paper towels, then place in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salad dressing mix (pour right from the envelope) and bacon (coarsely chopped).
Transfer the mixture to a shallow baking pan and bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9-inch).
Beat all ingredients until smooth for 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with whip cream.

title: potato rolls
directions: Prepare potatoes and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix well 2 cups sifted flour and yeast.
Mix potatoes with remaining flour.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Microwave peas for 6 to 8 minutes and rinse with cold water.
Flake tuna in a large bowl.
Add pasta, peas and remaining ingredients.
Serve with tomato wedges.

title: super spritz cookies
directions: With electric mixer at high speed, cream butter until soft. Add sugar gradually, continuing to cream about 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour in 3 additions; mix well by hand or with electric mixer after each addition; dough will be stiff.
Shape dough into 2 rolls; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Put in electric cookie maker or put by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with colored sugar if desired.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 400° or until just starting to turn light golden around edges, being careful not to overbake.

title: brandied chicken and peaches
directions: Cook chicken with diced onions in margarine.
When cooked, add orange juice and brandy.
Cook about 3 minutes or until sauce starts to reduce.
Add peaches and continue cooking 2 minutes. Sprinkle with green onions when ready to serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until set or just beginning to brown.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Put fruit with juice in saucepan and add dry jello.
Bring to a boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese. Mash with a fork; add ice cream and stir until melted.
Refrigerate until solid.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: christmas bonbons
directions: Roll into ball size of large marble.
Chill overnight.
Next day, melt 1 square paraffin wax and 1 large bag chocolate chips. Dip bonbons in the mixture.
Use a toothpick to hold while dipping. Drop bonbons onto wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: horse roll-ups
directions: Cream cream cheese and horseradish together.
It is up to on the amount of horseradish to use (up to 1 tablespoon).
Spread mixture on corned beef and roll up.
Freeze and then cut in 1/2-inch rounds.
Serve.
Can make ahead and freeze.
Ready when needed.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate to partially set (about 10 to 15 minutes). Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream last. Chill until firm.

title: lime chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add chicken. Cook until lightly brown on both sides. Reduce heat and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until done. Remove chicken to platter. In skillet, add lime juice and cook until bubbly. Add butter. Cook until thickens slightly. Stir in dill and chives. Return chicken; heat for a few minutes longer. Serve over cooked rice.

title: lemon custard meringue pie
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter.
Add flour and mix until smooth. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add lemon juice, then gradually stir in milk.
Cook in double boiler on medium heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Put on top of pie.
Bake until light brown in 350° oven.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cornish hens tarragon
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil and hens, in a food processor. Blend until smooth. With machine running, gradually add oil until mixture is thick. Cut the hens in half and remove the backbone. Rub the mixture into the hens and marinate at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: egg nests(great for brunch and lunch)
directions: Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Remove crust from bread.
Place one bread slice in each muffin cup; push down gently so it looks like a cup with 4 corners.
Drop a raw egg into each cup. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top each egg with 1/2 teaspoon of butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until eggs are cooked and bread is toasted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seacoast salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add all ingredients, mix and chill.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in blender and blend.
Add next 3 ingredients (including onion quarters) and blend until thick. Great dressing for spinach or fruit salad.

title: roach recipe
directions: Add water to form a soft dough and place small amounts around where needed.
This works very well.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Add
water, bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans, add ham bone and 3
quarts
water
to beans.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Remove bones
from
broth and when cool enough to handle, trim meat from bones.
Add ham, onion, celery, carrots and seasonings.
Simmer for
hour or until beans are done.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Just before serving add spinach leaves.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together brown sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg. Wash, peel and slice apples. Prepare fresh bread crumbs and toss with melted butter or margarine. Butter a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Arrange alternate layers of apples, bread crumbs and sugar mixture. Combine water and lemon juice and pour over top of the mixture. Cover the casserole and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove cover and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve hot, plain or with cream. Serves 4 to 6.

title: ginger's onion and potato soup
directions: Peel and chop approximately 12 potatoes.
Put them in a large pot with enough water to barely cover them.
Slice onions in large sections no smaller than quarters.
Put them on top of the potatoes.
Do not add water to the pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and pepper, 1 teaspoon of chopped red pepper and 1 teaspoon of garlic powder.
Once the onions are cooked until they are clear, smash the potatoes.
Reduce to low heat.
Do not drain the water.
Add butter, 1 to 2 cups milk and 4 to 8 ounces sour cream.
Top with shredded cheese.
Serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix together onion, bell pepper, soups and tomatoes.
Soften tortillas in broth where chicken was cooked.
Layer chicken, tortillas, soup mixture and chilies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pie
directions: Add juice and milk and beat.
Add cake coloring; fold in cherries and whipping cream and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill!

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in strips, brown in butter (low to medium heat).
Add 2 cups of water and beef bouillon cubes.
Slice onion and pepper and mix with steak.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash according to package directions; drain.
Lightly grease 7 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Mix the squash, chopped onion and soup and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Soak crushed graham crackers in pineapple.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Pack in loaf pans lined with wax paper. Decorate with nuts and cherries.
Keep wrapped for 2 weeks.

title: sole with rosemary
directions: Place the sole in baking dish so that the fish fits snugly. Prepare a mixture of the olive oil, lemon juice, wine, parsley and rosemary.
Mix the ingredients and pour over the fish.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until the fish barely begins to flake.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour rest of ingredients except for beef stew into dish.
Spoon beef over the top (do not stir). Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange glazed yams
directions: Cook yams in salted water until fork-tender. Cool.
Peel and cut off ends.
Cut each yam crosswise into 4 slices.
Place in a shallow casserole.
Peel oranges and slice each crosswise into 4 slices.
Place on top of yams.
Heat butter, orange peel, corn syrup and salt.
Pour over yams and oranges. Bake in a 325° oven about 40 minutes, basting twice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini-potato casserole
directions: Layer in 2-quart casserole in this order:
1/2 the potatoes, 1/2 the squash or eggplant, tomato or tomato sauce, green pepper, remaining squash, oregano, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese as desired and remaining potatoes.
Salt each layer, especially the squash.
Cook 15 minutes in microwave on High (if no carousel, turn 1/4 turn every 5 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix ingredients.
Line baking dish with 8 pork chops.
Spoon dressing mixture onto chops.
Place remaining chops on top of dressing.
Sprinkle top of chops with Shake 'n Bake.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until it's brown.
Serves 8 people, two thin pork chops per person.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Brown onion and celery in bacon fat.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper; allow to boil for a few minutes.
Add potatoes.
Heat thoroughly before serving.
Crumble bacon over the top.

title: banana bars
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in separate bowl and set aside. In large bowl, cream butter, both sugars and vanilla. Beat in bananas and egg. Gradually beat in flour/baking powder/salt mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Spread into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy round steak
directions: Dredge meat in flour. Season with salt and pepper. Brown meat in large skillet; add cider, onions, spices and sugar. Cover tightly and cook over low heat 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: lemon garlic chicken(slow cooker or crock-pot recipe)
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken and pat dry.
Mix oregano, seasoned salt and pepper together and rub all into chicken.
Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Transfer chicken to slow cooker.
Place water, lemon juice, garlic and bouillon granules in skillet used to brown chicken, scraping and incorporating all bits from bottom of skillet.
Pour over chicken and cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, stir in the parsley and cook on high.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except haddock.
Cut haddock into 1-inch blocks.
Pour the mixture over the haddock and simmer 20 minutes.
Dip haddock in melted butter.
Absolutely delicious.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in mixing bowl. Dissolve soda in sour cream. Bring butter or margarine, cocoa and hot water to a boil; let cool. Mix vanilla, eggs and cinnamon well. Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour into a greased 15 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: aronowitz fruitcake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients; add to fruit mixture.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Spoon into greased brown paper lined 8-inch pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil 3 minutes the water, sugar, raisins, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, shortening and salt.
Cool.
Add dry ingredients and stir. Bake at 350° in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Test.
May be eaten plain or frosted.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place carrots and onion in layers in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt; top with bacon pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry jellied salad
directions: Combine and set in refrigerator until firm.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble biscuits and cornbread into a 20 lb. roaster pan. Add all other ingredients, mix well and bake in 350° until celery and onions are cooked and tastes done in the middle of the pan, or about 2 hours.

title: orange cabbage slaw
directions: From the orange, grate enough zest to measure 1 1/4 teaspoons. Squeeze the juice.
Place zest and juice in a large bowl. Discard squeezed orange.
Whisk in vinegar, sesame oil and salt until well combined.
Add green and red cabbage, scallions and carrots.
Toss well to combine.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving to blend flavors.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Simmer beans 1 hour.
Fry bacon until crisp and wilt onion in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add other ingredients and crumble in bacon.
Pour in baking dish and cover with 1-inch crushed cracker crumbs.
Cut one stick of oleo on top and bake at 400° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits, water and salt.
Add oleo and cheese.
Stir until both are melted.
Cool slightly and add beaten eggs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerated bran muffins
directions: Mix both brans and salt.
Add boiling water; stir.
Add buttermilk; stir.
Allow to cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time.
Next, add flour and soda.
Finally, add the bran.
This can be kept in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.
(Note: Do not stir after taking from refrigerator to put in muffin tins.) Fill 2/3 full; bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: apple-cream coffee cake *
directions: Mix pecans, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Grease well 9-inch tube pan.
Beat butter until creamy at high speed; gradually add remaining sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda.
On low speed, beat flour mixture into batter, alternately with sour cream. Spread half of batter in pan, top with thinly sliced apples.
Top with half of pecan mixture; add remainder of batter, then pecan mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until well done.
Remove cake from oven, let stand in pan on wire rack for 30 minutes. Loosen cake and lift out base.
Let cool.
Loosen from base and tube and lift to plate.
Serve hot or cold.
Keeps moist, freezes well.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake until browned, about 35 minutes.

title: instant sweet sliced pickles
directions: Mix pickles, green pepper, onion and salt; let stand for 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: crunchy party mix
directions: In a saucepan, heat together the oil, Worcestershire, garlic salt, seasoned salt and several drops hot pepper sauce.
In large roasting pan, combine the cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Stir oil mixture well and drizzle over the cereal mixture, tossing to coat evenly.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with Parmesan and toss lightly.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half if using whole breasts.
Wipe with damp paper towels.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, celery salt, paprika, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, coating each piece well.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together	sugars,
oleo
and
oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.	Sift
dry
ingredients	and
add
to first mixture; mix well.	Roll in small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press down with a glass dipped in sugar.
(Can be colored sugar.)
Bake
minutes	at 375° or until golden brown.

title: molded apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling juice and add apricots and remaining cup of juice.
Heat to almost boiling; pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Immediately cover with marshmallows; chill. Top with sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with the cheese at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix in order as given.
Roll in ball.
Flatten with glass (dipped in sugar).
Bake at 325° until golden around the edges.

title: chimichanga dish
directions: Chimichangas in baking dish.
Heat the beans and chili together and pour over top, then layer grated cheese, onion, black olives and last the salsa on top.
Heat 30 minutes at 450° or until bubbly hot.
Serve with sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding(not a bread)
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Check with toothpick to see if it's done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place broccoli in a 1-quart casserole. Evenly combine mayonnaise, chicken soup, eggs and cheese in mixing bowl.
Pour over broccoli, gently pressing down between spears. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped corn and tomatoes
directions: In a 2 quart casserole, stir together tomatoes, kernel corn, cream corn, eggs, flour, sugar and pepper.

title: new potatoes and white sauce(thickened potatoes)
directions: Peel or scrape enough new potatoes for a mess. (If preferred, leave the skins on.) Cut large potatoes in half or quarter. Boil until tender. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Mix flour with a little cold water and add to pot; stir to make gravy. Just before serving, stir in dried parsley.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Into a bowl, sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in caraway seed.
Cut in butter until coarse, like cornmeal.
Stir in raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine buttermilk, 1 egg and soda.
Stir into flour mixture until just moistened.

title: hobo stew(as served in the hobo jungles)
directions: In a pot, put the nail, vegetables (except garlic) and meat. Cover entire mix with beef or chicken stock and cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Drain and reserve stock.
Add garlic and Tabasco sauce.
Remove nail and make a roux.
Add the stock over the meat and vegetables and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven for 30 minutes (not done in jungle).
Serve on a hot plate.

title: chocolate covered banana pops
directions: Peel bananas; cut each into thirds.
Insert wooden sticks; place on wax paper covered tray.
Cover and freeze until firm. Melt chocolate chips in double boiler with shortening.
Remove bananas from freezer just before dipping; dip each piece in chocolate.
Be sure to cover completely allowing excess to drip off.
Immediately roll in chopped peanuts.
Put them back on wax paper and cover; return to freezer.
Serve frozen.
Makes nine pops.

title: trash
directions: Melt ingredients and pour over 8 cups (12 ounces) Rice Chex cereal.
Shake in a small garbage bag.
Pour 2 cups powdered sugar over mixture and shake again.

title: harvest bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine above ingredients until creamy. Press into 9-inch square pan.
Bake 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat butter and
peanut
butter until light.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar
and	cream well.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, baking
powder
and
salt and mix well.	Add chocolate chips and
vanilla.
Spread
batter
into sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Pour over remaining ingredients.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs on rack in baking pan.
Brown in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn and brown on other side for 10 or 15 minutes. Drain fat and put ribs in slow cooking pot.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Cover and cook on low six to eight hours.
Makes five to six servings.

title: golden carrot bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine the oats, cereal flakes, flour and baking powder.
Stir in the carrots, raisins and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, whisk together the water and dry milk until smooth. Whisk in maple syrup, egg whites and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix until just combined; do not overmix.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm to touch; turn off heat, leave in oven with door ajar for 2 hours.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt in water.
Let set overnight; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 3 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, rice, raisins, egg and pudding mix. Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Pour into dessert dishes.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted margarine, 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth.
Add whipped topping and mix well.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Refrigerate.
Mix jello in pineapple juice until dissolved and add strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese and chill overnight.

title: ham and noodle casserole(large)
directions: Cook noodles and combine all ingredients.
Microwave 15 minutes on High, 30 minutes on Medium-low.
Stir once.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done; cool and take off bone, cut into pieces.
Put broth over crumbs; beat eggs and add to crumbs.
Add baking powder and rice.
Fold in chicken last.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Easily serves 12 to 15.

title: sausage macaroni stir-fry
directions: Prepare macaroni as per package instructions.
Drain well. In skillet, heat oil.
Add sausage and carrot; stir-fry 1 minute. Add next 5 ingredients; stir-fry until tender.
Stir in macaroni. Heat well.
Serve in heated bowl.

title: joni salad
directions: Mix jello; cool.
Add fruit and put in bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Spray a nonstick baking cookie sheet with non-stick cooking spray.
In a large bowl combine the potatoes, 1/4 tsp. salt and the sugar with cold water to cover. Soak for 15 minutes.
Drain and blot dry.
In another large bowl toss the potatoes with the oil and paprika.
Place in a single layer onto the baking sheet.
Bake, turning the potatoes over as they brown, until cooked through and crisp, about 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 tsp. salt.

title: frozen pink clouds(individual salads)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place mixture into individual cupcake cups.
Freeze until solid.
Makes 24 to 30 individual servings.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Stir in cooled chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon mixture into a cooled baked pastry shell. Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: chip dip
directions: Drain chicken and mash with a fork.
Add chili and cheese. Cook in a crock pot or pan.
Cook slow.

title: my chili
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Add kidney beans, white beans, whole tomatoes and tomato soup with 1/2 cup water.
Stir in contents; add chili pepper as needed for taste.
Cook for 15 minutes and serve.

title: sea gull's droppings
directions: Mix and put in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
(Does not brown.)
Serve with crackers.

title: fig bars
directions: Beat well the butter, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix with butter mixture.
Chill 1 1/2 cups figs or ground dried fruit with 1 cup water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook 3 minutes; chill.
Take dough and cut in half.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness in stripes about half as wide as length; spread filling down center.
Turn edges over to center.
Pinch together tight. Place on baking sheet cut side down.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Remove.
Cut in 2-inch slices.

title: date loaf
directions: Combine milk, coconut, vanilla wafers, marshmallows and nuts together in large pan.
Mix all ingredients together (best with hands).
Then make a square loaf on Reynolds Wrap.
Put in refrigerator overnight or until ready to eat.
Slice from end of loaf.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear each biscuit into 4 quarters.
Roll each piece in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Place pieces in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cook the butter, remaining sugar and cinnamon until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese reach room temperature.
Add pimento cheese and garlic salt; mix with mixer.
Chill until firm.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: kugel
directions: Boil noodles for 6 minutes, then drain.
Add butter to noodles.
Separate eggs.
Take yolk and mix with sugar, cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla flavor and lemon juice.
Add white raisins to mix.
Beat and fold white of eggs.
Pour in dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Chop or grind cabbage and carrot.
Add sugar, vinegar, and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Cream well.
Add all the other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chilled marinated carrots
directions: Scrub carrots and peel, if desired.
Cut carrots in half crosswise, then cut into long slices.
Cook carrots in small amount of boiling salted water in covered saucepan until just tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss with carrots.
Chill, covered, for several hours.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls out like pie crust on a large cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven and cool.
Mix cream cheese at room temperature (soft) with dressing mix.
Add mayonnaise; mix well and spread on baked, cooled crescent rolls. Top with the chopped vegetables (either mix all together or layer them), adding tomatoes separately (last).
Then top with shredded cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and press lightly to hold vegetables in place.
Chill for 2 hours or more.
Cut in small pieces for hors d'oeuvres or larger pieces for lunch.
Enjoy.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Melt butter to lukewarm; mix nuts, coconut, sugar and milk. Add butter and vanilla.
Roll into little balls and place on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Stick a toothpick into each ball.
Put in freezer about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Put ham slices between paper towels to dry.
Mix other ingredients together to spreadable consistency.
Spread mixture on ham slices, roll and stick with 5 toothpicks.
Refrigerate overnight and slice between toothpicks.
Serve attractively.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water.
Drain.
Place in baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt and egg.
Spread evenly in pan.
Saute ground beef in oil. Drain off fat.
Stir in sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Layer in pan and top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter, margarine, butter flavoring, almond flavoring and vanilla together
Add sugar and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and put in large microwaveproof bowl.
Mix in another glass bowl the brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt. Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and cook for another 3 minutes. Add vanilla and soda.
Pour over, a little at a time, the popcorn. Stir and mix well.
Cook in microwave for 1 minute on High. Stir again.
Pour rest of sauce over popcorn.
Cook again for 2 minutes.
Then cool on cookie sheet.

title: "any" quick cobbler
directions: Use 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan (depending on how much fruit you have).
Spread 1/3 of cake mix (dry) on bottom of pan.
Spread half of fruit on top.
Sprinkle another layer of cake mix over fruit.
Spread remaining fruit and top with remaining cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour and mix in. Shape with hands.
Pat into 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes or until golden and lightly brown around edges. Cut into squares.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine juices, salt and sugar in saucepan.
Heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Serve piping hot.

title: fruit delight
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and juice.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish 2 inches deep.
Cover with fruit and juice. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Crust rises to top of fruit.

title: pepperoni puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Starting at short side, tightly roll.
Pinch dough to seal.
Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch one side on each.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple sugar-free pie
directions: Mix in microwave bowl.
Zap 3 minutes; stir.
Zap 3 minutes; stir.
Zap 1 minute.
Stir and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: chicken and green chili enchiladas
directions: Place tortillas in oven.
Heat oven to 425°.
Mix chicken, 1 cup of cheese and chilies in a bowl.
Mix enchilada sauce, water and sour cream in a 2-cup measure.
Spread 1/2 cup of sauce mix on bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Remove tortillas from oven. Spoon 1/2 cup of the turkey mixture down center of each tortilla. Roll up to close.
Set enchiladas seam side down in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce mixture over enchiladas.
Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes longer until cheese melts.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate.
Combine milk, soda and vanilla; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in round prepared pans or 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Ice with favorite chocolate icing.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Cook
sugar,
cocoa, milk and syrup to soft ball stage. Add butter
and cook 1 minute.
Add vanilla; beat until right consistency
to
spread.
If
you like, add one cup of chopped nuts.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer remaining ingredients (veggies).
Add sugar to mayonnaise; spread over salad.
Top with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease baking pan. Slice apples thin and put in pan with water. In a bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon. Melt margarine and pour over dry ingredients. Stir until it crumbles and sprinkle over apples. Bake 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad with rosemary
directions: Thinly slice the celery and combine in a bowl with the chicken.
Blend together the mayonnaise, sour cream and rosemary. Pour the dressing over the chicken and celery.
Stir until the ingredients are well-coated.
Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate to serve later.
Serves 4.

title: herb grilled fish
directions: Mix dressing, milk and seasonings; refrigerate.
Place fish on greased grill over low coals (coals will be ash gray) or rack of broiler pan.
Grill or broil 2 to 4 inches form heat for 6 to 8 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with dressing mixture.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: tuna-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix mayonnaise, dressing and mustard.
Add all ingredients and garnish with egg.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more. Keeps well.
Serves 8.

title: almond mushroom rice
directions: Saute almonds in butter.
Add mushrooms and rice.
Stir until hot.
Serve as a side dish.

title: beans-n-rice that fill you up
directions: In nonstick pan, heat oil; add 1 cup onion and 1/2 cup green pepper and cook until tender.
Add rice, cumin, red pepper and coriander.
Mix and heat 2 minutes.
Add beans; heat.
Add uncooked onion and tomato if desired.
Approximately 125 calories per 1/2 cup; less than 2 grams of fat.

title: fancy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onion in large skillet until meat loses color and onions are tender.
Drain only if excess amount of fat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole dish at 375° until brown.

title: elegant luncheon chicken
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add soup, mushrooms and chicken. Heat and stir.
Then add sour cream.
Don't boil.
Serve in patty shells (frozen).

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat, then fold in blackberries with some juice, making 2 cups.
Pour into cake pan greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Insert a toothpick when it comes out clean, it is done.

title: hot salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes with food chopper. Mince peppers with food chopper. Slice green onion very finely. Mince garlic and cilantro. Chop 1/2 white onion with food chopper. Squeeze limes and lemon into mixture. Add salt to taste. Mix all together. Refrigerate. Serve with chips of your choice.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt butter in small cast-iron
skillet.
Stir together well the cornmeal, flour, egg and
buttermilk.
Add the melted butter, leaving a small amount of butter
in
bottom and along sides of skillet.
Pour mixture into
heated
skillet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: leg of lamb with cucumber sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut slits in lamb and insert dill and garlic slivers.
Roast for 2 1/2 hours or 30 minutes per pound. Brush mint jelly over meat the last 10 minutes of roasting time. Remove meat from oven to rest.

title: dirt
directions: Combine cool whip, cream cheese, pudding, vanilla, milk and powdered sugar.
In a large container, alternate between layers of crushed oreos and pudding mixture; beginning with the oreos and ending with the oreos.
Refrigerate.
Can put in a flower pot with flower stems wrapped in plastic wrap as a centerpiece.
Or in sand buckets and dish out with shovels.

title: frozen log
directions: This is delicious for hors d'oeuvres or great for lunch when spread on a split English muffin, then broiled.
Put all through a food chopper.
Mix and shape into a log that is 2 inches in diameter.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Slice and put on Melba rounds or your favorite cracker.
Put under broiler until brown.

title: breakfast loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an ungreased loaf pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 325°. Let set 10 to 15 minutes after removing from oven. Excellent with blueberry muffins.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and sugar; press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, spread mixture of Eagle Brand milk and coconut.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Frost with chocolate frosting, candy bars or chocolate chips.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add food coloring, water and oil.
Cook in heavy pan for 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan. Cool and knead.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: crab meat surprise
directions: Drain crab meat and flake over cream cheese.
Pour sauce over crab meat; serve with your choice of crackers.
This is a quick appetizer to prepare for unexpected holiday company.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Add milk and other ingredients.
Drop out on wax paper.
Yields 3 dozen pieces of candy.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, then add diced onion and simmer for a few minutes.
Add chili block or mix; mix well.
Add tomatoes and chili beans and approximately 1 can water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: linguine with italian sausage
directions: In a skillet, pour olive oil.
Add onions and peppers and saute.
Add sliced sausage and canned tomatoes.
Turn heat to low and simmer.
Follow directions on package of linguine to cook. Drain linguine.
Serve skillet mixture over linguine.
Yum, yum, yum, yum....
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.

title: three layer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Cool to lukewarm; add cheese.
Pour on second layer. Chill until firm.

title: marinated tomato salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, pepper, onion and celery in bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix vinegar, water and salt and pepper.
Add to tomato mixture.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all and pour into a floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs. Add tomato sauce, onions, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Add venison and mix well. Press into an ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Combine brown sugar, mustard and vinegar. Pour over meat loaf. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix well; boil 5 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Mix with 1 box powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain off all liquid; mash.
Beat together egg and milk; add to squash.
Mix cheese, oleo and cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 to squash mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: nutty cream puffs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pat out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and onions in 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet until tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat, stirring to form soft curds. When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and Cheese Sauce.
Spoon eggs into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/4 cup melted margarine and crumbs, mixing well; spread over egg mix. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook sliced potatoes until just tender; drain.
In separate saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add 3/4 of the cheese and blend well.
Mix cheese sauce with potatoes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, pecans and onions. Spread on ham slices and roll. Place in refrigerator over night. The following day slice and place on a tray to serve.

title: ice tea syrup(homestead's version of ice tea)
directions: Boil
loose tea in water 2 minutes; strain and add sugar and lemon juice to the tea water.
Stir until sugar dissolves. (This makes
a
syrup,
which
can be refrigerated and kept as needed as
long as two weeks.) To serve ice tea, add 1 cup tea syrup to 4 cups water and mix well.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix peaches and sugar together in a blender.
Add to other ingredients.
Churn until frozen.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: small one egg cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and flour mix alternately to sugar and shortening mixture which has been creamed.
Add egg and beat smooth.
Cook in greased and floured cake pan.
Makes one layer.
Can be frosted or used with sauce.

title: fast fixin' fruit and cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour the cooking oil in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Tilt pan so oil covers the bottom.
Mix cake mix, water and eggs, using a mixer.
Pour into pan with oil and blend. Spoon pie filling over batter using a fork to create a marbled effect.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Serves from pan.
Cover tightly.

title: mexican dip
directions: Heat on low. Crock-pot has to be on low.

title: o' henry cookies
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, salt and vanilla. Add oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: french butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl combine sugar, soda, cream of tartar, salt, vanilla, butter and egg.
Mix with mixer on low speed for about 1 minute or until well blended.
Gradually add flour; blend at low speed until well mixed.
If desired, tint with a few drops of food coloring.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Using a pastry blender, cut in shortening to the dry mixture until it resembles coarse meal.
Store in an airtight container.

title: butter cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add slowly alternating with milk.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion mixture, hash brown potatoes and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Spoon potato mixture into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cereal.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add flour and seasonings.
Stir until smooth; slowly add hot milk, stirring when it thickens.
Melt cheese in sauce.
In buttered baking dish, put layers of sliced potatoes, onion and cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas two-step chicken picante
directions: Mix picante sauce, sugar and mustard. Place chicken breasts in a 2-quart shallow baking dish. Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve over rice.

title: barbecue cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, oats, cheeses, eggs and catsup to make a loaf.
Put loaf in pan; coat loaf with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 400° until done.
For a smaller loaf, cut ingredients in half.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix well. Blend in 1 cup of the chopped nuts. Mixture will be soft. Chill until firm; shape into a ball. Roll in remaining nuts. Place on serving plate and press the cherry into the top. Serve with crackers.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix sugar, dates and 1 stick margarine. Cook over low heat. Stir until melted. Stir in the Rice Krispies and pecans. Make into balls. Dip in powdered sugar. Good!

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: In large pan, mix cocoa, sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to boil.
Boil until soft ball stage forms in cold water; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, quick oats and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cookies harden as they cool.

title: slow-cooked spaghetti sauce
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Transfer to a slow cooker. Add next 10 ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours or until heated through. Discard bay leaf. Serve over spaghetti. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
By hand, beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in pineapple and fold in bread cubes.
Bake, uncovered, sprayed with Pam, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Press most of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the cranberry sauce and rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture until crumbly.
Beat separately water, vinegar and egg.
Add water, vinegar and egg mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened and dough is formed.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1 stick margarine.
Press firmly into cake pan (oblong or square).
Add 1 cup chopped pecans on top of this. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with the oil.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tourtiere(pork pie)
directions: Roll half pastry crust and fit in a 9-inch pie plate.
Brown pork and onion, skim off excess fat and mix in soda crackers, water, apple and spices.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill pie plate.
Cover with other half of pie crust.
Cut holes in center of pie crust.
Bake on center rack of oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: spring rhubarb cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the margarine and stir in the milk, pecans and orange peel.
Drop biscuits on top of rhubarb mixture and bake in hot oven for about 25 minutes.
Serve with cream or milk if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked peaches and cream
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange peaches, cut side up, in an 8-inch pan.
Pour reserved cup of syrup over all. Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon and sprinkle over the top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve warm with small scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine evaporated milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla, blending well.
Pour into pie shell and bake on bottom rack of oven at 400° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
One pie.

title: beans and greens
directions: Simmer escarole in water until cooked down.
Drain.
Saut garlic in hot oil.
Add chicken broth, pepperoni and escarole. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add beans the last 5 minutes.
Add crushed red pepper to taste.

title: mexican chips and cheese
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Put in cake pan. Pour in refried beans, rice, enchilada sauce, 1 1/2 cups of cheese (save 1/2 cup cheese for top).
Mix in 1/2 bag of Doritos (save 1/2 bag for top).
Top with leftover cheese and Doritos. Heat until cheese melts and serve.

title: quick and easy taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Spread over cream cheese.
Pour picante sauce over layer of beef.
Sprinkle cheese over entire mixture. Microwave 10 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook on medium heat.
Boil 1 minute slowly.
Stir in at least 1/2 the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Then blend into the balance of hot mixture.
Boil 1 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat
and add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: *Oil may be purchased at pharmacy stores.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and pour 1/2 of the batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over first half of batter.
Pour remaining batter over this mixture. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Remove from pan and glaze while hot.

title: play dough
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a heavy aluminum saucepan.
Add next three ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Cook at low temperature for three minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead slightly.
Store in airtight container.
(A few drops of oil of wintergreen may be added to give a pleasant aroma.)

title: kish(this recipe is for deep dish pie crust.)
directions: Add all ingredients to deep pie crust and bake about 40 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish (oblong).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add milk, butter, egg yolks and vanilla; mix well and cook over double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue.
Cook at 350° .
Beat egg whites well until they form a peak.
Stir in 1 tablespoon sugar and place on top of custard mix in pie shell.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute onion and livers in chicken fat.
Put sauteed onion and livers, seasonings, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and eggs in blender and blend until smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups pate.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Place chopped dried beef in the bottom of casserole dish. Wrap bacon around chicken.
Arrange on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve over rice.

title: one meal dish
directions: Place each pork chop on a 12 x 12-inch square of foil.
Peel and slice 1 medium potato and carrot; slice green pepper and onion.
Add as many as desired.
Place 1 tablespoon of butter on top of onions, salt and pepper to taste (garlic, if desired). Seal foil tightly and bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Open foil when finished and place cheese; let it melt.

title: debra's quick pasta casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook pasta per directions on box.
Wash and chop all the vegetables.
In large skillet, cook squash, zucchini, bell pepper and onion in cooking oil and water until tender.
Mix half of sauce into vegetables; bring to boil.

title: joyce adams' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a fork to stir.
Mix well. Bake in pan which has been sprayed with Pam (9 x 12-inch) at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus vinaigrette *
directions: Cook and drain asparagus; arrange in shallow dish.
Mix all other ingredients except egg and gherkins in jar; shake well to combine.
Pour over asparagus.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, turning spears several times.
Arrange on platter, sprinkle with finely chopped egg and gherkins.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, ginger and cloves. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the mixture. Pat down with a spoon. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, then with the melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done (check with a knife coming out clean). Drizzle with powdered sugar icing or serve with whipped cream. UMW-good!!!

title: microwave snack cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine butter or margarine, oats, flour, brown sugar, eggs, walnuts and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup morsels.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in an oblong cake pan sprayed with Pam for 30 minutes at 350° or until knife put in the center comes out clean.
Cool well.

title: shrimp shells
directions: Divide crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Cut each into 3 triangles (24).
Clean shrimp.
Melt butter.
Mix in thyme and marjoram.
Coat shrimp with butter mixture.
Place one shrimp on each triangle.
Fold over.
Brush remaining butter over crescent triangle.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Dissolve thoroughly.
